title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Add flour mixture to batter and beat well. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip ball into sugar and arrange, sugar side up, 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until cracked on top.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Saute onions in melted butter.
Add shrimp and cook until pink. Add soup, water and potato.
Season with salt, pepper, bell pepper and Kitchen Bouquet.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add onion tops and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Serve over rice. Yield:
6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Spray a 9x9 pyrex dish with cooking spray for easy clean up. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In bowl, mix corn starch and sugar together.
Mix in eggs and milk until well blended, then add cream corn.
Last put in dish then dollop with butter on top.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake 1 hour or until set in center.
Very easy to make and very good.

title: kringles from norway
directions: Mix sugar, egg, sour cream and vanilla. Mix flour, soda and salt.
Blend thoroughly into cream mixture.
Chill 2 hours.
Form a modified figure 8 ring.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly golden.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: *One package (10 ounces) frozen, chopped broccoli, thawed and drained, can be substituted for the fresh broccoli.
Do not cook. Also cauliflowerets can be substituted for broccoli.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in pot of water.
Boil until tender.
Drain off water and cool. Cut into pieces.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cracker crumbs and continue to spread each ingredient in order listed, except Eagle Brand.
Slightly warm Eagle Brand and pour over top layer of nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: granny's dough
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into refrigerator.
Pinch off as needed to make biscuits.
Be sure to let cold dough rise before baking.
Grease the pan.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: ham delight spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread. Cut rolls in half; spread filling on half and top with the other half.
Put back into foil pan. Wrap with foil and heat at 350° until mixture is melted. Good to freeze ahead.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Simmer crawfish (in pieces), celery, onions, peppers and butter until seasonings are done. Add soup, pimento and cheese. Season to taste with red pepper. Serve with Melba rounds or assorted crackers. Makes 3 quarts.

title: shrimp feta stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry tomatoes, rock shrimp and oregano in butter or oil. When shrimp turns pink, add sherry and feta cheese.
If more sauce is desired, add up to 1/4 c. chicken broth.
Toss shrimp and feta with hot pasta.
Season with black pepper and serve.

title: brown sugar oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together in large bowl the oats, flour, baking powder and salt.
Whisk together in a small bowl the eggs and brown sugar.
Add the egg mixture, milk, oil and vanilla. Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients; stir well.
Batter will be soupy.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 16 to 18.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in baking dish; set aside.
Heat 1 cup sugar and water until sugar melts.
Set aside.
Mix remaining butter into flour.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn out on board and knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll out into 11 x 9 x 1/4-inch thick.
Spread berries over dough; sprinkle with cinnamon and roll up like jelly roll.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place into pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around slices.
Crust will absorb liquid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Before removing from oven, sprinkle 2 tablespoons of sugar over crust.
Serve warm or cool with cream.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion (can also add celery, bell pepper or mushrooms, if desired) in butter until tender.
Cook fresh or frozen broccoli in saucepan until tender.
Combine Cheez Whiz, soup, rice (uncooked) and milk.
Heat until almost boiling.
Remove from heat; cover for 5 minutes.
Drain broccoli.
Combine in casserole with other items. Season to taste.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Enjoy.

title: six layer dip-avocado dip
directions: Peel, seed and mash avocados. Stir in garlic powder, garlic salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Spread evenly in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Carefully spread the sour cream over the avocado mixture. Drain the picante sauce and layer over the sour cream, followed by a layer of olives, a layer of cheese and a layer of tomatoes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook together until broccoli is very tender.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a small saucepan.
When melted, stir in approximately 4 tablespoons flour.
Mix to form a soft smooth paste.
Stir into boiling vegetable mixture.
You may add 2 to 3 cups mild Cheddar cheese at this time if you like broccoli cheese soup.
Stir well and boil for a couple of minutes.
Add 2 quarts half and half. Immediately turn burner to simmer.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: chili meat balls
directions: Stir in all ingredients and add meat last.
Make balls less than 1-inch in size.
Bake in 350° oven 12 minutes.
Serve with cocktail sauce (chili sauce and horseradish).

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly by hand.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream together the eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: double chocolate cupcakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; make a well in center of mixture. Combine orange juice, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Spoon into paper lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately; cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: tuna snack
directions: Mix drained tuna with Thousand Island salad dressing and Louisiana hot sauce and serve on crackers.
Quick and easy snack.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder; pour in buttermilk before stirring.
Add shortening, then stir.
Pour on floured board and knead.

title: two by four soup
directions: Cook slowly for approximately 1 hour.

title: sour cream gravy
directions: Slighlty brown the flour in a heavy skillet over medium heat. Watch carefully, stirring constantly, then stir in butter.
When mixture is thick and bubbly, slowly stir in milk.
Reduce heat to low, stirring constantly.
When mixture is heated through and is beginning to thicken, add sour cream and season to taste.
Heat through, but do not allow to boil.
Serve with Verinikas.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, soda, salt, oatmeal, flour, nuts and vanilla to creamed mixture and mix well.
Make 2 or 3 rolls in waxed paper.
Let set in refrigerator overnight. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma flo's coconut pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt in a double boiler or heavy saucepan.
Gradually add scalded milk and cook over hot water until it starts to thicken.
Add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks and return to mixture.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beach cake
directions: Mix cake mix, nuts, margarine and 1 egg.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
A good dip for chips or vegetables.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine juice, sugar, eggs and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Stir in pineapple, celery, apples and pecans.
Fold in cream.
Pour in 9-inch square pan.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Optional:
I cook my mixed vegetables in with chicken broth.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in small bowl in microwave or in double boiler over stove.
Add butter and honey.
Serve over ice cream.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine baking soda and 1/4 cup buttermilk.
Stir and set aside.
Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour; measure and sift 3 more times. Add to batter alternately with 3/4 cup buttermilk.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Stir in baking soda-buttermilk mixture. Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Batter may also be baked in 2 greased 9-inch round pans for 40 to 45 minutes.
May be served alone or topped with fruit and/or ice cream.

title: baked pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into pieces and put in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over pretzels. Make sure you coat all pretzels.
Bake in a 200° oven for 2 hours.
Put in container.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and cocoa gradually.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Let stand in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Prepare thickening by adding just enough water to make a smooth, thick paste.
Slowly add to chicken mixture, stirring often.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add eggs last.
Put in large baking dish and cover with pastry 1/3-inch thick.
Press pastry against sides of dish.
Cut several slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Brush with melted butter.

title: fruit and cheese kabobs
directions: You will need 2 to 3 toothpicks.

title: jerry cooks...shrimp
directions: In a skillet, saute garlic, onion and celery in the oil.
Add sliced butter and the spices.
Turn to low; add the bell pepper and cover.
In a small saucepan, combine the rice and water.
I use no salt, but a pat of butter as I believe there is enough salt in the spices and the shrimp.
Bring rice to a boil; stir.
Turn to low and cover.
Do not even look for 12 to 13 minutes.
Trust me, if it is low it will not burn.
Two minutes before the rice is done, uncover the skillet; move the vegetables to one side so that you can fry the shrimp about 2 minutes on each side.
When rice is done, uncover and stir with a fork and recover.
Let set a minute. Add the tomato.
Serve rice in the middle of a large plate, spread into a ring; scoop the vegetables into the ring and top with the shrimp.
Serves 2.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs. Sift flour, cocoa and salt together; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Let cook for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour marshmallows over top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes (no longer).
Cool cake for 1 hour, then frost.

title: poppy seed fruit salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges. Drain pineapple (but reserve 1 tablespoon pineapple juice).
If using strawberries, cut them in half. Core apple and cut into bite size pieces.

title: good punch
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Before serving, can add pineapple sherbet in punch bowl.

title: carrot bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Add salad oil, vanilla, carrots, raisins, coconut, eggs and vanilla. Mix in nuts until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: special cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add flour, meal and sugar.
Beat to remove lumps. Add oil, buttermilk and eggs last.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.
(I use muffin pans.)

title: microwave fudge
directions: Add all ingredients (except nuts).
Do not stir.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and blend, adding nuts.
Spread in dish.

title: california chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground meat with onion; drain. Place meat and onion mixture in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole. Season to taste.
Add corn as next layer.
Pour evaporated milk over corn.
Top with the mashed potatoes, being sure to seal the edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Make pudding mixes as directed. Freeze candy bars.
Cut cake into 3 layers.
Crumble 1 layer into bottom of large bowl.
Put several tablespoons Kahlua on it. Spread 1/3 chocolate pudding over cake.
Spread 1 container Cool Whip.
Top with crumbled candy bar (1).
Repeat layers.

title: chocolate eclair dessert(very easy - very good)
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, place one layer of graham crackers.

title: dyed cinnamon pears
directions: Slice each pear into fourths and peel them.
Take food coloring and cinnamon and combine.
Shake well.
Add sugar.
Put pear slices into jar and pour food coloring mixture.
Fill jar to the top with water.
Let stand overnight.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, stir together sugar, flour and cornmeal. Add eggs and beat until ivory color.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice and butter; beat just enough to mix.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or cold and top with whipped cream.

title: chicken bake(fast and easy)
directions: Place everything in a baking dish.
Pour a little water, 1/2 cup, around outside edges of dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes (uncovered).
Serve with green beans and applesauce.

title: deep south cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese; gradually add sugar and one egg at a time.
Beat after each one.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Then nuts, vanilla and salt.
Bake in a floured and greased Bundt pan at 325° for one hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes and turn out.

title: mrs. duncan's dressing for slaw
directions: Mix
oil, sugar and salt.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Pour over slaw and serve.
Dressing will keep well.

title: beef stir-fry broccoli and vermicelli
directions: Saute onion.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, oyster sauce, parsley and water.
Cover; cook for 5 minutes until broccoli is tender, but still crisp.
Slice beef into thin slices.
Add beef and vermicelli to skillet.
Continue heating and stirring until meat is done.

title: monster chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
Break chocolate into squares.
Set aside 1/2 cup pecan halves.
Coarsely chop remainder.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Beat butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar in a medium bowl, until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and then chopped pecans.

title: crunchy sausage balls
directions: Soak pecans in hot water for 5 minutes.
Water should be as hot as you can get it from the faucet.
Put on terry towel and pat dry; while still moist, sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 240° for 1 hour.

title: ziti with onions and parmesan
directions: Melt the butter/margarine and cook the onions over low heat until they almost change color.
Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
Cook pasta until it is al dente.
When the pasta is almost done, return the onions to heat and stir in the beaten eggs.
Remove from heat.
Drain the pasta and stir in the cheese and onion sauce.
Serve at once.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Blend in eggs.
Add margarine, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 35 minutes or until set.

title: red wine vinegar and oil dressing
directions: Combine ingredients, shaking to mix well.
Salad oil may be used but olive oil (the more the better) adds a good flavor. Refrigerate in a tightly covered jar.
Makes one quart.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix nuts, flour and oleo.
Press into oblong cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes; cool.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix puddings and milk and spread on cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip and chopped nuts or chocolate swirls.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix sour cream, bananas and baking soda together.
Combine all dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix beaten egg yolks, sugar and Crisco well for about 2 minutes at medium speed.
Alternately add mashed banana mixture and dry ingredients to the sugar mixture.
Mix about 2 to 3 minutes more.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
If making loaves, reduce baking time to 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Cook green peppers in small amount of water, salted in saucepan until tender; drain.
Blend butter and flour in saucepan; stir in milk gradually.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add peppers.
Pour into baking dish; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir corn syrup, sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
When mixture boils, blend in butter.
Stir often after 230°.
Add nuts at 280°.
Stir constantly to 305°.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour out onto buttered cookie sheets.
Allow to cool.

title: beer biscuitslubbock, texas
directions: Add beer to mix and sugar.
Fill muffin tins (greased well) about 2/3 full. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: lace cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheet with crackers broken in half.
Boil sugar and butter until homogenized.
Pour over crackers sprinkled with nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Add dry ingredients to margarine, sugar and egg mixture, then add fruit.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: albondiguitas(meatballs)
directions: With gloved hands, remove stems, seeds and membranes from chilies; chop chilies.
Mix chilies, beef, egg, bread crumbs, milk, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into 1 inch balls. Place them in ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Cook uncovered in 400° oven until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Place meatballs in chafing dish.
Pour Salsa over meatballs.
Makes 36 meatballs.

title: pork tenderloin saute
directions: Pound pork medallions flat.
Saute capers and garlic in small amount of olive oil. Add pork.
Saute until pink is gone. Remove meat, swish a little wine and reduce.
Pour sauce over meat and serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat the eggs and add sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Cook until thick.
Keep it stirred or it will stick to the pan.
Add vanilla. Line a bowl with vanilla wafers.
Add sliced bananas and pour 1/2 the custard over it.
Add another layer of wafers, bananas and the rest of the custard.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Cook carrots in 1/2-inch boiling, salted water for 10 minutes. Combine crackers, salt, onion and pepper.
Alternate layers of carrots and crumb mixture.
If any carrot liquid is left, spoon over top.
Pour butter over carrots and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and cream to boil on medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until ball forms when dropped in cold water or soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp wiggle
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Stir flour into butter.
Add salt.
Stir milk in slowly.
When thickened, add shrimp, peas and curry. Serve on cooked pastry shells or tarts.

title: flour fritters
directions: Start with about 1 cup flour.
Add enough water and then egg and salt to make a batter the consistency of cake batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat and cook until brown.
Good to eat with molasses or lima beans.

title: great salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in container with tight lid.
Shake well before using.
A tart dressing.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherries in bottom of cake pan.
Place half of dry cake mix on top of cherries.
Next spread can of pineapple on, then the other half of dry cake mix.
Slice the butter and place on top. Then sprinkle the chopped pecans on.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Bring carrots and onions to a boil.

Cook until tender; drain. While carrots boil, melt cheese and margarine in double boiler. Combine carrots, onions and cheese mixture in casserole dish. Sprinkle brown sugar and crumbled crackers on top before baking. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For large functions (church dinners!) double this recipe.

title: ham casserole
directions: Simmer onions and celery in fat until tender.
Add soup, water and rice.
Mix well and cook 15 minutes on moderate heat.
Stir in meat, and place in greased casserole.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel apples and potatoes.
Layer 1/2 of these with 1/2 of marshmallows.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle 1/2 over top of layer.
Repeat to make a second layer of apples, potatoes, marshmallows and cinnamon mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator to make natural juice.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan in layers as follows: Start by pressing the uncooked hamburger firmly into pan (be sure to cover the bottom).
Crush onion rings and sprinkle over hamburger.
Put drained green beans over onion rings.
Pour mushroom soup over beans.
Sprinkle cheese over beans.
Top: Put Tater Tots in rows over entire mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Mix sifted dry ingredients and walnuts together.
Combine egg, applesauce and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Bake in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar. Add milk and butter; bring to boiling. Continue boiling until a soft ball is formed when a small amount from a spoon is dropped into cold water. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Allow to stand until fairly cool. Beat until creamy and pour into buttered pan.

title: scotchies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Remove from heat; add sugar and blend.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 13-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: saucy chicken and rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter; blend in flour.
Add tomato, chicken, cheese and basil.
Stir until the cheese is melted. Serve over rice.

title: vegetable medley salad
directions: Cut up spinach or lettuce.
Add a bit of chopped onions.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry; drain.
Add vinegar and sugar, about equal quantities plus a little water to skillet.
Boil and pour over the greens and cover so they wilt.
Serve as salad.

title: pinto hamburger casserole
directions: In a large frypan, brown hamburger; drain grease.
Put onion in hamburger and simmer.
Mix pintos, tomatoes, salt, pepper, hamburger and onion.
Put in loaf pan.
Make corn bread and spread over casserole. Bake until brown at 400°.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas in crust.
Mix Eagle Brand and lemon juice; pour over bananas.
Add pineapple.
Add pecans.
Add coconut; cover with Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Add cherries to top.
Chill and serve.

title: quick hamburger salisbury
directions: Make hamburger into patties.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper or whatever seasonings you prefer.
Brown in skillet.
Add 1 cup water and bouillon cubes and the can of mushroom soup.
Stir until blended.
Simmer for 15 or 20 minutes.
Serve with noodles, rice or whatever you prefer.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, gelatin, 1 cup sugar and water in a saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil.
Cool.
Cut up peaches; add a few drops of lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix with gelatin. Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: easy taco dip
directions: In a medium bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Stir until well blended and chill.
Serve with assorted chips or vegetable dippers.

title: salmonettes
directions: Open can of salmon.
Drain 1/4 cup juice into measuring cup. Add baking powder.
it will foam, which is what it is supposed to do.
If it does not foam, your baking powder is probably old, but will not hurt recipe.
Add egg; stir.
Add flour; stir.
Use teaspoon to drop into hot oil, turning once.
Place on paper towels to drain.

title: strawberry fool
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, milk and condensed milk; beat until smooth.
Add pie filling, pineapple, nondairy whipped topping and pecans; mixing well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or smaller baking dishes to freeze.
Cover tightly with foil and freeze until needed (keeps well for 6 weeks).
When ready to serve, remove from freezer 1 hour before needed.
This makes slicing easier.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks with milk, lime juice and coloring.
Pour in cooked crust.
Bake 40 minutes. Top with whipped topping when cool.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix hamburger with 1/4 cup soup.
Add onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into six patties. Put in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spoon off excess grease.
Now, combine remaining soup with water and pour over steaks.
Return to oven for an additional 10 minutes.

title: sunshine refresher
directions: Combine 1/4 cup juice and Marshmallow Creme in electric blender container or mixer and blend until smooth. Add remaining juice and eggs; beat until foamy. Serve with orange slices.

title: brownie chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of spring-form pan. Prepare brownie mix as directed for chewy brownie mix.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until set.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; stir in chips.
Pour over brownie and bake for 50 minutes at 300°.

title: tallerini
directions: Brown meat, add onion, pepper, and garlic on high heat (in large electric skillet).
Add the rest of ingredients as listed. Cover, stir after 3 minutes.
Cover again.
Reduce heat to simmer and simmer 45 minutes or until noodles are done.
Serve with warm biscuits.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well; heat in pan and pour over meat.
Bake for another 1/2 hour.

title: east coast grill cornbread(goes well with chili for a crowd)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil or Pam 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix flour, corn meal, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
In separate bowl mix eggs, oil and milk.
Pour eggs, oil and milk over dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and stir until just mixed. Bake approximately 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean. Cornbread should be brown on top.
Makes 12 large, thick pieces.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill greased loaf pans 1/2 full and bake for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; whip until thoroughly blended.
Add clean snow (not packed) until no more can be added, then eat!
It can also be stored in the freezer.
Here is a recipe which young children would thoroughly enjoy, both in preparation and consumption.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Mix the dressing mix and 1/4 cup melted butter. Combine. Stir over low heat until moist.
Spoon over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Mix sifted dry ingredients and nuts together.
Combine egg, applesauce and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 50 minutes in 350° oven.
This nut bread stays moist for some time.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 sticks butter.
Add flour and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes (until golden brown).
Cool.
Place in fridge or freezer for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore(microwave)
directions: Cut large pieces of chicken in half for uniform size.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in 4-quart casserole; stir in chicken pieces, coating with sauce.
Cook covered 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve plain or over spaghetti.
If desired, use 1/4 cup red wine for part of the water.

title: estonian cake
directions: Put softened butter into a large bowl and mix with mixer.
Add sugar and mix again until well creamed.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well each time.
Mix flour, salt and soda together and mix into butter mixture with sour cream.
Add vanilla extract and nuts.
Mix again with mixer.
Add raisins to the mixture, stirring slowly with a large spoon until evenly mixed.
Pour the mixture into a buttered tube or Bundt pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven (350°).
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Let cake cool for one hour in pan.
Turn onto a plate, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Guten Appetit!

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough in 1/4-inch slices.
Place and press together to fill greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes until done.

title: dream muffins
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon into 12 well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, oleo and salt well.
Mix in powdered sugar to make stiff dough.
Chill 2 hours.
Make into balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Chill again.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls with a toothpick into melted chocolate. Place on wax paper or cookie sheet.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean. Fast and delicious.

title: tangy glazed mackerel
directions: Cut fish into serving size portions. Place in baking dish. Combine all remaining ingredients; blend well and pour over fillets. Turn to coat. Marinate 1/2 hour (no more). Drain; put sauce aside. Arrange fish, skin side up, on greased broiler pan. Brush with remaining sauce. Broil 4 to 5 minutes. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil in skillet.
Boil until it comes to a soft ball in cold water.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Beat until there is no gloss.
Spread on wax paper until cool.

title: basic buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut 1/3 cup butter into flour with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface; knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch round cutter and place on a baking sheet.
Bake biscuits at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Brush with melted butter. Yield:
10 biscuits.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Lightly grease pie plate (10 x 1/2-inch).
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until brown; drain.
Spread in pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.
If using size 9 x 1/4-inch pie pan, lower milk to 1/2 cup and eggs to 2.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Mix other ingredients in butter and marshmallows.
Pack in a container.
Set in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.
Freeze part if you need to.

title: maui milk punch
directions: Gradually add fruit juices to soften ice cream, stirring until blended.
Stir in milk.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve a large package of strawberry Jell-O in boiling water; add cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened; add sour cream and pecans and mix well.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sissy's fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix, then place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: peach (or apple) crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread pie filling in 8-inch pie plate. Toss together cereal, cinnamon and melted butter in bowl.
Spoon over filling.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly and topping is lightly browned.
Serve warm with ice cream if you wish.
Serves 4.
(406 calories, 4 gm.
protein, 15 gm. fat, 173 mg. sodium, 23 mg. cholesterol)

title: orange pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Makes 1 Bundt pan and 1 loaf.

title: chocolate munchin cake
directions: In 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, stir together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Stir with fork, scraping corners and sides of pan, until mixture is uniform.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken, cut in pieces.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix well all the other ingredients except cheese and onion rings. Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, then add onion rings. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: steak and rice
directions: Saute steak, onion and celery in oil.
Drain oil off and add other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If it becomes dry, mix a beef bouillon cube in a cup of boiling water and pour over casserole.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup,
milk,
chicken,
half
the chopped onion and jalapenos.
In a medium saucepan, cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Dip
each tortilla in boiling water until soft, then add a handful
of
cheese and some onion to the center of each tortilla; roll up
and place in a baking pan.
Pour sauce over tortillas and
sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
May be prepared ahead of time, but do not pour sauce on until ready to bake.

title: coney island spuds
directions: Bake potatoes in oven at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes or on High in microwave for 10 minutes.
Mix meat and sauce.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in half the dip and 1/4 cup water.
Heat, but don't boil.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Mix on low speed until well blended. Combine sugar (for topping). Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: 4 day cake
directions: Combine, cover and refrigerate first mixture.

title: carol snow's open-faced cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together with equal amount of mayonnaise and catsup, just enough to hold the cheese together.
Spread on whole wheat hamburger bun halves.
Place the buns on a cookie rack on a cookie sheet (this makes the bun bottoms crisp).
Bake at 350° to 400° until cheese is melted.

title: cream puffs
directions: Spray a baking sheet with nonstick spray coating.
Bring water, margarine and the 1/4 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add flour all at once, stirring vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add the 4 eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition. Drop batter by heaping tablespoons, 3-inches apart, onto a baking sheet, making 12 mounds.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Cool.
Split cream puffs and remove any soft dough from inside.

title: chicken canapes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on crackers.

title: glazed ham
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and set aside.

Allow your ham to cook for one hour and a half, basting with its own juices. In the final half hour, pour the mix glaze over the entire ham. Then place whole pineapple rings with toothpicks over the entire ham and let finish baking in its last half hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and cook in baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar corn cakes
directions: In small nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add green onions and pepper and cook over medium-high heat.
Cook about 1 minute. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: yaki soba
directions: Fry meat, onions and carrots.
Mix water and soy sauce together.
Add seasoning packages from noodles.
Then add noodles, cabbage, mushrooms, celery and green pepper.
Cover and cook until water is absorbed.

title: chocolate covered coconut(candy)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Chill in freezer for several hours.
Make into small balls (bonbon size).

title: coconut toast
directions: Spread butter on 1 side of each slice of bread.
Beat together egg and sugar; add salt.
Beat until a smooth paste; add enough coconut to the paste to make a spread.
Spread coconut mixture on buttered side of bread, all the way to the edges.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: blue ribbon granola(minnesota state fair, 1978)
directions: Melt together margarine and honey.
Stir in remaining ingredients except raisins and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Stir frequently.
Add raisins and refrigerate.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together, then add dry ingredients. Add apples and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: potatoes anna
directions: Melt butter and salt.
In a greased 9-inch pie plate, arrange potato slices, overlapping them.
Drizzle butter mixture on top. Cover plate tightly with foil.
Bake 25 minutes, covered; then bake 55 minutes, uncovered, or until potatoes are tender and crispy. Let stand at room temperature for 5 minutes before serving.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into patties.
Brown well on both sides.
Pour off grease.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Cook slowly until done.

title: rich peanut butter bars
directions: Flour pan.
Melt peanut butter in a saucepan.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour in pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry flavored preserves made with figs
directions: Cook medium to low heat.
Figs can be peeled, but not necessary.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cut up apples and nuts; set aside.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar. Beat well and add vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda, baking powder; add to liquid mixture.
Add apple and nuts; mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix and bake in greased, covered casserole for 1 hour at 350°. Grated cheese may be added during the last 10 minutes.

title: pear and cream cheese salad
directions: Drain pear halves, reserving the juice.
Add just enough of the juice to the softened cream cheese to make it easy to mix with the nuts; should be able to hold its shape very well.
Place pear half, cut side up, on a bed of lettuce.
Fill with the cheese mixture and top with half a maraschino cherry.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and resift 3 times with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and beat until soft and smooth.
Add vanilla and egg yolks one at a time and beat until fluffy and light.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately, beginning and ending with the flour, and stir well after each addition.
Fold in graham cracker crumbs and stiffly beaten egg whites alternately.
Pour batter into two 8-inch layer pans with bottoms lined with thin plain paper and bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes or until frosting tests done.
Good with peanut butter frosting.

title: california spuds
directions: Mix all ingredient in large bowl.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch (or larger) pan.
Add spices to top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Add tuna to macaroni.
Add relish, boiled eggs and mayonnaise.
Mix together.
Add more mayonnaise, if desired.
Season to taste. Refrigerate.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: zucchini or bean casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add stuffing to make crumbs.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole, 1/2 of crumbs and filling with balance other 1/2 of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat oil. Add flour until brown. Add onion and garlic. Saut for a few minutes. Slowly add tomato paste. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook for 15 minutes. Season to taste. Serve with grits and bacon for breakfast or for lunch. Serve with rice or spaghetti.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Pour over cocoa and sugar.
Stir until blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Press into large sheet pan and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cut as desired.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Take cookie dough and roll into balls.
Place in mini cupcake liners.
Place liners in cupcake or mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Immediately push peanut butter cup down in center.
Let cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs until light; add mixture of sugar, flour and salt and beat until well blended.
Add buttermilk, lemon juice and melted oleo.
Mix until smooth, then pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake in hot oven 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is set. (Center may be slightly jiggley.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cut the roast into quarters; place in a greased 5-quart slow cooker. In a bowl, combine barbecue sauce, preserves, green pepper, onion, mustard and brown sugar. Pour over roast. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender. Remove roast and thinly slice. Return meat to slow cooker and stir gently. Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes longer. Skim fat from sauce. Serve beef and sauce on rolls.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan and bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute. Meanwhile mix the following together:
oats, cocoa, vanilla, nuts and peanut butter.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto wax paper; let cool. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: dressing for cabbage
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 2 minutes.
Add celery and mustard seed. Pour over cabbage.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled. (I also add carrots and onions dry.)

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on round pizza pan and cook until done; let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar and spread on cookie. Creatively place fruits of your choice on top.

title: cashew-butter crunch
directions: Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch round baking pan with foil. Butter the foil heavily.
Set pan aside.
In a 10-inch skillet, combine cashews, butter, sugar and syrup.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is melted and mixture turns golden brown, stirring constantly (about 8 to 9 minutes).
Quickly spread mixture in pan. Cool for about 15 minutes or until firm.
Remove candy by lifting edges of foil.
Peel off foil.
Cool thoroughly.
Candy may be left as a disc or broken into pieces.
Makes about 1/2 to 3/4 pound.

title: squash custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spice.
Add squash, milk and egg. Pour into casserole dish.
Microwave for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add flour, milk and salt.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Stir in potatoes and onion.
Divide batter into floured and buttered 9-inch pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Melt sugar and butter in a skillet.
Add apples and saute until soft.
Divide apples evenly over pancakes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops and clean seeds out of peppers.
Place whole cleaned out peppers in salted boiling water.
Boil 5 minutes; drain.
Saute beef and chopped onion.
Add Spanish rice and catsup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Top with cheese. Cover and bake in 350° oven until done, about 25 minutes.

title: fluffy dip
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients with a mixer.
Serve with strawberries, apples, pears, or kiwi.

title: eggplant rollatini
directions: Wisk together 2 eggs, 1/2 tsp. salt, 1/2 tsp. pepper, 3 Tbsp. Parmesan cheese until blended.
Dredge eggplant slices in flour, then in egg mixture.
Heat olive oil in a large deep skillet until hot, but not smoking.
Place eggplant slices in the hot oil and fry for a minute or two on each side until golden.
Remove from skillet and blot on paper towels until cool enough to handle.
Place ricotta or cottage cheese in a bowl and mix with remaining egg, salt, pepper, parsley and mozzarrella.
Mix well.
To stuff eggplant:
Place one slice of eggplant on a clean, flat work surface.
Place a heaping spoonful of cheese mixture on the center of the eggplant.
Beginning at the wider end of the eggplant, roll up like an eggroll.
Repeat with remaining eggplant and ricotta mixture.
Pour 1 cup marinara sauce and 1/2 cup water into a 9 X 12 inch baking dish.
Place eggplant rolls side by side and top with remaining marinara sauce.
If desired, place a piece of pepperoni on top of each roll.
Cover baking dish with foil, and bake in 350 degree oven for about 25 minutes, until bubbly around edges.
Let cook about 5 minutes before serving with a salad and side of pasta.

title: mini quiche lorraine
directions: In bowl, blend butter and cream cheese.
Stir in flour.
Shape into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients except bacon.
Set aside.
Preheat grill.
Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Place in ungreased muffin cups.
Press evenly in bottom and up sides of each cup.
Bake with hood closed until light golden brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Fill each cup with 1/4 cup egg mixture.
Top with bacon.
Bake with hood closed until center is set and slightly puffed, 20 to 25 minutes. Rotate pan once.

title: simple cheese cake
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Pour into crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and whipping cream.
Add egg yolks, beaten. Fold beaten egg whites into mixture.
Crush graham crackers very fine and spread half over bottom of baking dish.
Spread the butter and egg mixture over the crumbs.
Add the pineapple, then the whipped cream.
Top with remaining graham cracker crumbs. Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: sage cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch cast-iron skillet. In a mixing bowl, combine all the dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine vegetable oil, eggs, buttermilk and milk.
Pour into the dry mixture.
Blend quickly with a wooden spoon. Do not overbeat.
Stir in the corn kernels.
Pour the batter into the skillet. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and serve warm.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Soak the fruit mixture in wine overnight.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, sifted flour and salt.
Then add fruit mixture and nuts.
Grease three loaf pans and line with heavy brown paper and a layer of waxed paper.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Temperature may be raised to 275° during last half hour.
Place a pan of water on the bottom shelf of oven until last half hour of baking.

title: vegetable ranch dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Grate vegetables in blender. Drain well. Mix vegetables with cream cheese, and dressing mix with a mixer.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add can of crushed pineapple with juice and pie filling.
Pour into serving dishes. Top with Cool Whip.

title: oreo smush
directions: Make crumbs out of 24 cookies in food processor or crushing. Pat crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan; drizzle melted margarine over crumbs. Heat topping in jar in microwave until hot. Cut ice cream in 3/4-inch slices and place on cookie crumbs evenly. Pour hot topping over ice cream. Put in freezer for 10 minutes to cool. Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs. Cover. Keep frozen in freezer.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on muffins.
Place on cookie sheet in freezer for one hour.
Cut in half or quarters. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: turkey soup
directions: *Turkey bones may be cooked for broth, or you may use the instant chicken broth mix.

title: coconut fudge
directions: Combine sugar, whipping cream, butter and vanilla in a medium saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook uncovered until mixture reaches thread stage (230°). Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.

Beat mixture at medium speed of mixer 2 to 3 minutes or until fudge is thick and begins to lose its gloss. Pour 1 tablespoon fudge into paper lined miniature muffin pans. Sprinkle coconut evenly over each piece and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Yield:
about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add garlic, onion and celery.
Cook until soft.
Stir in tomatoes and next eight ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to boil, lower heat, cover; simmer one hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 10 minutes more until macaroni is tender.
Garnish with parsley.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To serve:
Mix 1/4 cup of Chocolate Mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: easy cake tastes like pecan pie
directions: Pour over crust and place in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly overnight and cut into bite-size squares.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake potatoes about 1 hour.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out potatoes.
Mix with butter and beat until fluffy.
Fold in cheese, sour cream and chives.
Put back into potato skins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Place all ingredients, except topping in blender.
Blend on high speed, stopping occasionally to stir, until smooth, about 3 minutes. Pour into plate.
Bake just until puffed and center is dry, about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Spread topping carefully over top. Cool.
Refrigerate until chilled, at least 3 hours.
Serve with fruit, if desired.

title: dilly willy crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in plastic container with seal. Marinate for 24 hours.
Stir often, keeping sealed between stirrings.

title: crescent roll lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add seasonings, tomato paste and Ro-Tel.

title: irish fruit bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour with soda.
Add to the egg mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Stir in cherries, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, well.
After mixing, add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Chill in cold place for an hour or two before rolling and cutting into cookie shapes.
Use floured surface to roll dough on.
If dough seems sticky, add a small amount of flour to dough; roll and cut.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until lightly browned on bottom.
Makes several dozen.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
Mix with hot water to taste.

title: sarah banana pudding
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until spoon coated.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour brown sugar into pudding to get a marble effect, then pour over bananas and wafers.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: french vanilla dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press in bottom of cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix sugar, cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Put cherries, blueberries, lemon or other pudding mix on top.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: andy's favorite cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients, covered, over medium about 10 minutes or until cauliflower is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Do not drain. Lightly mash, or chop the cauliflower into bite size pieces.

title: nashville squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain well.
Add all ingredients except crumbs. Put in casserole dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good!

title: peppered steak with sauteed mushrooms-italian style
directions: In 1/4 cup oil, saute green peppers, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares, and several slices of garlic about 5 minutes, turning them often to prevent browning.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 teaspoon oregano.
Cover and steam about 5 minutes, turning them several times.
Do not cook any longer than necessary.
Peppers should be crisp-tender and still green.
Put aside.

title: microwave rice
directions: Microwave water in a 2-quart microwave dish on High for 7 minutes or until water boils. Add rice and salt. Stir and cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir, re-cover and microwave on High 6 minutes. Stir again.
Let stand, uncovered, before serving.

title: diabetic gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325° in large bowl.
Beat egg with Sweet 'N Low.
Melt margarine in boiling water.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to egg mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into nonstick 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients to make cake batter.
Pour one-half of batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 of this mixture onto cake batter.
Spread remaining batter on top, then sprinkle with rest of nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crispy pie(low calorie)
directions: In a sprayed 9-inch pan add cereal.
Melt peanut butter and honey in microwave for 30 seconds.
Pour over cereal and freeze. Prepare pudding mix and pour over crust and freeze.
Thaw a few minutes before serving.

title: old-fashioned pickled okra
directions: Wash okra, leaving short stem on pods.
Pack in hot, clean jars.
Place 1 pepper and 1 clove of garlic in each jar.

title: crispy parmesan cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix crushed corn flakes, cheese, salt, paprika, onion powder and pepper in shallow pan.
Blend milk and oil in another shallow pan.
Dip chicken in milk mixture, then crumb mixture, coating all sides.
Arrange chicken in shallow pan. Bake until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.

title: red roasted potatoes
directions: Par boil potatoes, Drain. Place potatoes in glass dish.
Mix all other ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes. Add 1 tbsp. butter with olive oil.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 min.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve with Wheat Thins.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender.
Blend on medium speed.
Bake in a 10-inch greased pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together all but dressing.
Just before serving, toss dressing and salad together.

title: lazy stew(any size)
directions: Amount of ingredients are not given as you decide how much of each to use.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together and cook until thick and clear.
Let cool.
Add berries and fill baked pie shell.
Put in refrigerator.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Cream sugars and margarine. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well. Stir in bananas. Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla. Stir in nuts, if desired. Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° about 90 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate leaves(use for garnish)
directions: *Must be oil based.

title: flan
directions: Caramelize in a metal dish 3/4 cup sugar and 5 tablespoons water.
Carefully coat inside of receptacle with caramel (a stainless steel bowl is excellent).

title: mounds bar cake
directions: Using any good chocolate cake mix, prepare according to instructions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Divide cake in half when done and cooled.

title: ginger bars
directions: Combine first 7 dry ingredients.
Melt oleo; add beaten egg, molasses and water.
Blend with dry ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: mandarin lettuce salad
directions: Mix lettuce, oranges, onion and pepper rings.
Add sliced fresh mushrooms and avocado.
Toss with dressing just before serving. Top with walnuts.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli; drain.
Add creamed mixture.
Put in casserole; sprinkle the top with Pepperidge Farm filling mix. Bake at 375° until crumbs are brown.

title: fred brown's chili beans
directions: The secret to the taste of the beans is preparing the mix. Brown in skillet individually the ground beef, onions, pepper and celery.
Combine those ingredients with tomato sauce, tomatoes, ketchup, salt, pepper and chili powder.
You will need a large pot to combine these ingredients.
(Do not add beans yet.)
Let simmer 2 hours.
Now add the cooked beans and simmer another 2 hours, stirring frequently, so as not to burn.
Delicious!

title: sausage casserole
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish (greased) layer (first) croutons, (second) cheese, and browned sausage.
In mixing bowl, mix milk, mushroom soup and mustard.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour mixture over ingredients in the dish.
(You may put in refrigerator and bake later).
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with sugar, butter and flour.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Add liquid gradually to consistency desired.
Drop by tablespoons on a greased pan.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: brown sugar  sauce
directions: In saucepan, blend flour with sugar; add butter and milk and cook until desired consistency.
Stir in vanilla.

title: lucy owen's fresh apple cake
directions: Put in	mixer,	oil,
sugar,
eggs and flavoring.
Beat until creamy.
Sift
dry	ingredients
together.	Add
to
oil mixture, a little at a time.
Fold in chopped apples and nuts. Put into greased
and floured Bundt pan.
Cook about 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and put to side. Hand mix first 7 ingredients together, then add next 5.
Mix well Crisco and cornmeal.
On bottom of large iron skillet,
put 1/2 of the mixture, then add hamburger on top of that.
Then add the other 1/2 of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix according to package directions.
Spread cookie dough 1/8 inch thick on an ungreased pizza pan.

title: party dessert
directions: Cut together to make crust of flour, pecans and margarine. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef and potato pie
directions: Bake roast in water with onion, garlic, salt, pepper and coffee at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Boil potatoes in water 20 minutes, then mash.
Add milk and butter.
Combine flour and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture forms small crumbs.
Add water 1 tablespoon at a time until mixture forms ball.
Divide and roll dough into 2 rounds.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Using a fork, make holes to bottom of pan all over cake.
Using Jell-O, add 3 cups boiling water.
Dissolve.
Let Jell-O mixture chill in refrigerator, but do not set.
Pour liquid over cake, in holes and at corners.
Chill for 2 hours.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Keep chilled.

title: twist salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Blend well.
Set aside.
Mix noodles second time.
Pour other ingredients over tuna or noodles.
Mix well.
Serve cold.
Serves 6 or more.

title: goodies
directions: Bring Karo syrup, sugar and vanilla to a boil in saucepan. Add peanut butter and dissolve in hot syrup.
Pour mixture over Special K and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: candied carrots
directions: Clean and steam or boil carrots until tender, then add ingredients and cook until the syrup thickens.
Leave carrots whole.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and stir.
Chill overnight.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise if desired.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Chop in bite size pieces.
Place in 2-quart dish (lightly greased).
Mix dressing according to package directions. Saute onion and celery.
Add to dressing.
Place on top of chicken.
Mix together soups with 1/2 cup water.
Pour soup mixture on top of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy miniature cheesecakes
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Place one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake
liner, and fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Top with pie filling. Chill and serve.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn-gumdrop cake
directions: Combine butter and marshmallows in a large saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until melted.
Add popcorn, nuts and gumdrops; blend. Press mixture into well-greased pan (Christmas tree is used at Christmas, etc.). Chill and turn onto plate. Wrap with plastic wrap.
Makes nice gifts.

title: ham and cheese loaf
directions: Place slice of ham in baking dish.
Spread on top of slice 1 tablespoon chili sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue for size of loaf desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and place in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and roll into a loaf.
Bake in a medium oven for about one hour.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar and spices in a small bowl.
Add nuts to egg white a few at a time.
Coat them well.
Drop in bowl of sugar and spices.
Place on a buttered oven baking sheet.
Brown in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Simmer together carrots, onion and peas until onion is clear. Lay chicken in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with vegetables.
Pour on 2 cans of soup mixed with poppy seed.
Bake mixture at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place 8 biscuits on top.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.

title: marinated vegetable toss
directions: In a bowl, combine mushrooms, tomatoes and green onions.
In a screw-top jar, combine oil, wine, vinegar, sugar, basil and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover; shake well.
Pour over and toss with vegetables.
In a large bowl, toss vegetable mixture with spinach. Serve with grated, hard-cooked egg yolks over salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a lightly greased dish at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with nachos, crackers or bread (flat, pita or pumpernickel) or Blue Chips.

title: giant oat cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oats.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture by hand and mix until well combined.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Place 6 balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten to 3-inch diameter.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 17 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: fruit punch
directions: Prepare concentrate in advance.
Combines juices and sugar in a gallon container (I use thoroughly cleaned milk jugs).
Shake and place in refrigerator.	Prepare ice ring with sliced fruit and freeze.

title: basic biscuit mix
directions: Into a large bowl, mix all the dry ingredients well.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients with pastry blender or two knives until it looks like coarse corn meal.
Store in tightly covered container.
Will keep on pantry shelf.

title: baptist cookies
directions: Bring everything except coconut and Rice Krispies to a boil (2 to 3 minutes).
Cool.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Form into balls and flatten.
Roll in coconut.
If too soft, add more Rice Krispies.
You can press into pan and cover with coconut and when cool, cut into squares.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in dishpan.
Cook on top of stove for 30 minutes.
Stir so that is won't stick to pan.
Pack in jars.
Cook in pressure cooker at 5 pounds for 10 minutes.
This recipe makes 11 quarts.
This recipe can also be used to freeze soup instead of canning.

title: country chicken on biscuits
directions: In large saucepan, combine 2 cups water and bouillon until dissolved. Remove vegetables from pouch and add to broth.

Heat until thawed. Combine flour with 1/2 cup water; stir until smooth. Add to broth-vegetable mixture. Heat, constantly stirring, until thick and smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Serve over baking powder biscuits.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions in oil. Add chicken, chilies and 2/3 of each cheese. Fry tortillas in small amount of oil for 20 -30 seconds, just to soften them.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Stir until well mixed and loses gloss.
Pour into buttered pan and cut when slightly cool.

title: arizona bittinger's thanksgiving fruit cake with lola schoppert's
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add beaten eggs, then the molasses; mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk and beat until foamy, then add to other ingredients.
Measure the flour and add the spices to it and sift together 2 to 3 times.
Have the nut meats, raisins, currants and candied fruits in separate containers and take a couple of tablespoons of the flour and mix through each thoroughly.
Start adding a handful of each to the first mixture along with the flour until all is in, then mix well.

title: yummie yams
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel, slice and arrange in single layer in baking dish.
Mix together brown sugar, sugar, flour and salt.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle cinnamon over sugar mixture.
Combine water and vanilla.
Pour into pan. Dot potatoes with pats of margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dark chocolate frosting
directions: Combine the sugar, butter and milk in a small saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: schmara
directions: Mix milk, eggs, salt and flour into a medium batter.
Put about 1/8-inch shortening into a 12-inch frying pan.
Heat on high and pour in batter when pan is hot.
Stir constantly and break up batter until liquid is gone.
Lower heat to low and start cutting batter with a spatula.
Pour in 2 tablespoons farina a little at a time while cutting with spatula.
Turn heat back to medium.
Keep cutting until mixture breaks into little pieces and doesn't stick to spatula or feel doughy anymore.
Cut and turn constantly.
Let brown.
Sprinkle with sugar (1 tablespoon) and mix in.
When done, sprinkle more sugar on top and serve with canned peaches.

title: jigglers
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl, stirring 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Refrigerate 15 minutes or until gelatin is cooled to room temperature.
Remove bowl from refrigerator.
Using wire whisk, vigorously stir whipped topping into gelatin until smooth.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Dip pan in warm water for 10 seconds.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Lift from pan. Best when served cold.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay out crescent roll, unrolled on a jelly roll pan.
Bake until brown in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: tastes-better-than-it-looks casserole
directions: Brown pork sausage, drain grease.
Drain off juice from apricot halves.
Combine both with cream of mushroom soup and about half the noodles.
Dump the whole mess into casserole dish and cover with rest of noodles.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until heated through.

title: russian chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow casserole.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over chicken.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Baste occasionally.

title: oatmeal white chippers
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together flour and soda.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Add flour mixture; beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats, white chocolate and almonds.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes or until done.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute; remove and cool on a wire rack.
Makes 38 cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift meal, baking powder and salt together.
Mix water and milk and stir into dry ingredients.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then drop by teaspoons into deep Crisco heated to 365° or until bread crumb browns.
Fry until brown (3 to 5 minutes).

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes and turn oven to 325 degrees and bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
Brown, crumble and drain ground beef.
Add sauce to beef.
Spread 1/4 cup meat mixture over each noodle.
Sprinkle with 2 to 3 tablespoons cheese.
Roll carefully.
Place seam side down in baking dish. Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until heated through.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour.
Combine butter and flour, using a wooden spoon or your hands, until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Mixture will be quite stiff.

title: crab casserole
directions: Make a white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Mix together with other ingredients and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Delicious!

title: louisiana hot dip
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage together.
Combine other ingredients in saucepan; drain grease off meat and add to sauce.
Serve with nacho chips or pretzels.

title: easy prune cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add liquid ingredients.
No mixer is needed.
Bake in a well-greased Bundt or other cake pan. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: olive spread for crackers
directions: Cut up olives; stir into softened cream cheese.
Add juice as is needed.
Good Christmas color dish with your favorite crackers.
Stores well.

title: fresh apple-nut cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan. Thoroughly stir together flour, salt and soda or put in flour sifter and sift.

title: pear clafouti
directions: If using canned pears, place on paper towels to drain thoroughly.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs with electric mixer until foamy.
Add milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, rum extract, salt and nutmeg.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Spread pears in greased 10-quiche dish or pie pan.
Pour batter over pears.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream and poached pears is optional and not included in nutritional analysis.
Serves 8.

title: spritz cookies(cookie press recipe)
directions: Sift together flour and salt and reserve.
Measure butter and confectioners sugar in a large bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and blend well. Add food coloring as desired.
If dough becomes too soft, add a little bit more flour.
Fill cookie press with dough.
Shape cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. (Do not brown.) Cool.
These cookies freeze well.

title: chocolate bar dessert
directions: Melt milk and marshmallows in microwave or double boiler. Remove from heat.
Break candy bars into pieces and add to marshmallow mixture.
Stir until melted.
Cool until partially set. Fold Cool Whip into chocolate mixture.
Make graham cracker crust with the crumbs and melted oleo.
Put into 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Pour chocolate mixture over crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Fry by large spoonfuls until browned on both sides.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and cover until cheese is melted.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Place brisket in a large Dutch oven or soup kettle.
Combine next 10 ingredients. Pour over brisket.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 4 1/2 to 5 hours, until meat is tender.
Remove brisket and discard marinade.
Shred meat. Return to Dutch oven.
Add barbecue sauce and cook until heated through, stirring frequently.
Spoon on hamburger buns.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: honey chocolate frosting
directions: Stir dry ingredients together and place in mixing bowl with remaining ingredients except milk; mix until smooth.
Add milk and mix at low speed until light.

title: frozen cabbage
directions: Put salt over vegetables; let set 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Squeeze and add mixture.
Bring to boil. Cool.
Pour over shredded cabbage.

title: microwave roast lamb
directions: Variation:
Baste with orange juice instead of lamb drippings.

title: shrimp salsa
directions: Thaw shrimp per directions; drain well!
Can remove some of tomato skin if preferred before chopping.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Should be made 6 to 8 hours prior to serving.
Can double this recipe easily.
Lasts in refrigerator 2 to 3 days. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mary's chocolate fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese over low heat.
Add cocoa, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add tomatoes, sauce and spices.
Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish layer meat sauce, noodles and cottage cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese begins to brown.

title: onion soup
directions: Brown onions in melted butter until golden brown.
Add broth and water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil 10 minutes.
Add egg noodles; cook 30 minutes.
Add grated Swiss cheese and let stand until cheese melts.

title: frozen fruit whip
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend on high speed for about 3 minutes.
Place one dozen cupcake holders in a muffin pan. Spoon fruit whip into cups and freeze.

title: san antonio chicken with picante sauce
directions: Sprinkle both sides of chicken with cumin and garlic salt. Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and brown on one side about 5 to 7 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine beans, corn, picante or salsa and 1 teaspoon cumin.
Turn chicken over and spoon bean mixture over chicken evenly.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Move chicken to a platter.
Turn up heat under bean mixture and thicken.
Spoon mixture over chicken and serve immediately.

title: shrimp and wild rice
directions: Gradually add flour to 1/2 cup melted butter; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Gradually add broth. Cook until smooth and thickened; simmer 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pia colada cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions; cool. With wooden spoon, make holes in top of cake. Pour Coco Lopez over top of cake, then crushed pineapple with juice. Top cake with Cool Whip, almond slivers and coconut. Refrigerate.

title: quesadillas
directions: Grill tortillas with butter either in skillet or grill until lightly browned.
Sprinkle cheese on 1/2 tortilla and spread green chili on the other 1/2.
Add onion to taste and fold tortilla in 1/2 on grill.
Grill until cheese is melted.
Great for snacks!

title: french pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place heavy 10-inch or 12-inch skillet (cast-iron is best) in oven and heat until very hot.
In small mixing bowl put 2 large or 3 medium eggs and whisk until lemon colored.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup flour.
Whisk until blended. Cube (1/2-inch) 5 tablespoons very cold sweet butter.
Remove skillet; add butter to hot skillet.
Wait 5 to 6 seconds, until butter melts (can be slightly lumpy).
Quickly add batter to skillet and put back in oven.
Leave 15 minutes.
When crisp, remove from oven and sprinkle with 2 to 3 tablespoons powdered sugar; put back in oven until sugar glazes slightly (about 2 minutes).
Remove from oven; squeeze juice of 1 lemon over pancake. Slice and serve with fresh berries, honey or just plain.
(Don't panic when pancake sides rise above the skillet 3 to 4 inches.)

title: fruit dumplings
directions: Mix frozen fruit, sugar and water.
Put in electric skillet until soft.
Drop dough mixture by tablespoons on top of fruit and cook at a low bubbling (covered) for 20 minutes.
Remove lid and let set until liquid is absorbed.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix the corn meal and salt thoroughly and then scald with 2 cups of boiling water into which has melted 1 heaping tablespoonful of shortening or fresh bacon drippings.

Scald is the key word. This mixing of boiling water and fresh bacon drippings or shortening into the meal is a cooking process which produces a firm mound of dough, wet enough yet only malleable when cool.
Set aside to cool for about 20 minutes.
When the dough has cooled, work into it 1/2 teaspoon of baking powder, dissolved in 2 tablespoons of cold water.
Pinch off a piece of dough the size of half a duck egg.
Pat dough into a small round cake about 5/8-inch thick.
Work up the balance of the dough in little cakes of this size.
The little cakes can be fried immediately or stored in the refrigerator on wax paper to be cooked later.
You fry them in deep fat, hot enough to bubble immediately over the cakes (about 380°) until they are browned slightly.
Serve immediately.

title: crockett minestrone soup
directions: Saute celery, garlic and parsley in 1/4 cup olive oil.
Add refried beans and water.
Add tomatoes, cabbage and/or other veggies of choice and 2 teaspoons beef bouillon.
Cook 1/2 hour. Add 1 cup salad macaroni.
Cook until tender.
Enjoy.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon and set aside. Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and beat well.

title: peanut butter balls
