directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Shape into 24 meat balls. Brown meat in cooking oil in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Add meat and vegetables.
Bring to a boil or until vegetables are tender. Add parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Wash and deseed chillies (save juice).
Spray 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Line pan with chillies; add cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add flour, salt, milk and chilli juice.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set and golden brown.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans over bottom of a 9 x 13 pan sprayed with nonstick spray.

title: mom's buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks slightly; add to buttermilk, vanilla and butter (melted and cooled).
Add to dry ingredients; beat thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with mixer.
Soften cream cheese.
Add to marshmallow cream.
Add Cool Whip.
It will keep in refrigerator in an airtight bowl.

title: merry medley
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain before serving.
Serves 6. Contains 50 calories per serving.

title: baked green tomatoes(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange them, overlapping, in a lightly oiled oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Lightly brown crumbs in butter and combine with herbs. Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Top with cheese and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Mix all together; simmer for 3 hours and add water as needed.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening like pie dough crumbs.
Take out 2 cups of crumbs for top of pies.
To remainder of crumbs in bowl, add eggs, molasses and water.
Dissolve soda in 1/2 cup of hot water and add to other liquid mixture.
Divide liquid in unbaked pie shells.
Put crumbs on top and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 375° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake at 250° or 300° until set and knife comes out clean.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Melt butter in a large baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 200°. Add steak sauce, Tabasco and pecans; stir often while baking. Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with Cajun seasoning.
Store in airtight containers.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: cream taco casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat, onion and bell pepper; drain. Add garlic salt and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: sugar glazed walnuts or pecans
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, melt butter on Medium-high (microwave) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Mix well to combine butter and sugar.
Add nuts and mix to coat.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread out onto waxed paper and cool slightly. Serve warm or cold.

title: low-fat cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions, exchanging 2 egg whites for each whole egg and equal amounts of applesauce for oil.
This works well for any flavor cake mix.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients; add broccoli.
Pour into a greased frying pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let set a few minutes to firm up before serving.

title: cherries and nuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Add shortening, without stirring.
Combine milk and cherry juice.
Add 3/4 cup of this liquid and blend together mixture.
Add the remaining liquid and egg whites.
Blend well.
Add chopped cherries and nuts; blend.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put ingredients into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed.
While pasta is cooking, in a large skillet, saute garlic, onion, and green pepper in olive oil. Add tomatillo sauce, cumin, and black beans.
Mix well and allow to simmer for 5-10 minutes.

title: lemon butter sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in 2 cup glass measure.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until hot.
Stir. Serve with fish or vegetables.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Cook together sugars and milk, stirring constantly, until it reaches soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter is melted.
Add pecans and beat.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.
Cool until firm.

title: low-fat veal piccata
directions: Trim fat from cutlets; dredge cutlets in flour.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Add oil.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add veal and cook 3 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove veal from skillet; drain and pat dry with paper towel.
Transfer veal to a serving platter.
Keep warm.

title: turnip slaw
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients well.
Pour over turnips and toss well to coat.
Refrigerate several hours for flavors to blend.
Yields 4 servings.

title: skillet tuna casserole
directions: In medium skillet, heat tomato soup with water to boiling. Stir in rice, onion, green peppers, salt and marjoram.
Remove skillet from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove cover; fold in tuna.
Top with cheese slices cut into thin strips and olive pieces.
Cover.
Heat gently until cheese melts.
Nice with green beans with mushrooms.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: sugar coffeecake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, margarine and Crisco until fine.
Keep 1 cup aside for the topping.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Sprinkle the reserved topping on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with crushed pineapple; stir well.
Drain mandarin oranges and cut up; mix in oranges.
Mix in cottage cheese, then Cool Whip.
Stir in all ingredients.
Cool in refrigerator.
Makes large bowl.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Stir together Kool-Aid, sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and ice.
Ad 7-Up or Sprite just before serving.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook green peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain. Combine remaining ingredient together in bowl. Stuff peppers with meat mixture. Stand peppers upright in baking dish. Combine reserved soup with 1 can of water and pour over peppers. Bake covered at least 45 minutes in a 350 degree oven. Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: sour cream date cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Combine flour, salt, soda and nutmeg and then stir into creamed mixture. Stir in dates and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on sheets 5 minutes and then remove.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together and bake at 350° approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bopbop's oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small mixing bowl, pour boiling water over oats.
Allow to stand.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add the oats.
Sift together the flour, soda, spices and salt.
Stir into oat mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool completely. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: canned pickle beets
directions: Wash beets; cut leaves off.
Cook beets until tender.
Peel off skin.
Make a syrup with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil with beets and can by packing into sterilized jars.

title: easy microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place peppers in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Microwave, covered, for 5 minutes.
In a bowl, crumble beef, drained corn, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, onion, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Microwave, covered, for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon into pepper cups.
Spoon remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cook, uncovered, for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: eggs and sausage
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard; mix well.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer bread and small pieces of sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over this.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix as any pound cake.
Grease tube pan and flour.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.
Ovens may differ.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix flour and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cut shortening into flour until it is very fine.
Store in a covered container. Doesn't need to be refrigerated.
Makes 7 to 8 cups.

title: cornmeal peanut butter pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix orange juice and peanut butter together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until the batter is wet and lumpy.
Add more juice, if needed.

title: seafood stewgroves, texas
directions: Chop onion, celery, bell pepper and saute.
Add all tomato products.

title: peppery scallops
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
Rinse scallops with running cold water to remove sand from crevices.
Pat dry with paper towels.
In medium bowl, toss scallops with butter to coat well.
On waxed paper, mix bread crumbs, basil, seasoned pepper and salt.
Dip one flat side of each scallop into bread crumb mixture.
Place scallops breaded side up on rack in broiler pan and broil for 5 minutes without turning until bread crumb topping is golden and scallops are opaque.
Serve with lemon slices or wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise in half.
Remove the yolks.
Mash and blend with remaining ingredients.
Fill whites with the mixture. Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Layer in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish or large tray.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add pumpkin, oil and water. Blend thoroughly.
Add all dry ingredients.
Bake in soup or vegetable cans or standard loaf pan, filling them half full.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups boiling water, butter and oatmeal.
Let this mixture stand 20 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to oatmeal mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Combine sugar and margarine until smooth.
Add one egg and beat well, then add remaining eggs and beat.
Add flour, about 1/3 at a time.
Add vanilla and nuts and mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 27 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Cut into pieces and remove from pan.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large cooking
pot,
put
oil and soften the onion for 1 minute.
Wash
over beans.
Pour water into kettle, then beans, and cook over low
heat for at least one hour, or until beans begin to get soft.
(Pot should be covered.) Remove 2 or 3 tablespoons of beans
and
mash, then return them to pot and stir. Continue cooking
until
bean
gravy
becomes milky and thickened.
Cut sausage
into
pieces,
1 1/2-inches long, and add to beans
and
continue
cooking, covered, for 15 minutes. Never precook sausage.
This should be served over rice.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Dissolve sugar, salt and pepper in vinegar.
Add tomatoes, onions and bell peppers.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Bone and remove skin.
On each piece, place a slice of chipped beef.
Roll up and fasten, if necessary.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: coconut and honey cakes
directions: In a heavy saucepan over medium heat, bring milk and honey to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a bowl, combine the coconut, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Slowly add the milk mixture and stir until smooth.
Stir in the eggs until well combined.
The batter will be quite liquid.
Spoon the batter into 24 mini muffin pans lined with paper cups.
Fill each cup nearly full.
Each time you fill a cup, stir your batter.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool the pan on a wire rack.

title: hungarian cabbage and noodles
directions: Saute onion and cabbage until soft and cabbage is cooked slowly.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cook wide, curly noodles as directed on package.
Drain well.
Stir noodles into cabbage.
Add sour cream, if desired.
Cook 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chop suey
directions: Slice onions.
Cut up celery.
Simmer in bean sprout water in cans until tender.
When done, add bean sprouts.
Cook meat separately, then add to the first mixture.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Use flour to thicken.
Let stand a few hours before eating.
Much better the next day!
Serve over rice.

title: nanny's christmas ham
directions: Bake ham for 1 hour. On top of stove in saucepan, heat cranberry sauce, mustard and pepper. The more pepper the more it tastes like barbecue sauce. I use about 3/4 teaspoon to 1 can of sauce. Heat until smooth. Pour over ham, draining any water juice off of ham first. Bake for remainder of time, just cover ham, pricking with fork. Use the rest of sauce on the table for sauce after baked. Good.

title: christmas kraut
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cover.
Put in refrigerator and let set overnight.

title: philadelphia dutch pickles
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients and cucumbers in large pan. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes, no longer.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal with hot lids.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw dough; roll out into a rectangle.
Add pepperoni, cut up pieces of cheese, then mushrooms.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Pinch ends in good.
Put, seam side down, on a cookie sheet.
Make 3 slits on top of roll.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: heavenly broiled fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Place fillets in a single layer on a well-greased ovenproof platter (16 x 10-inch).
Brush fillets with lemon juice and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook pork and cut into small pieces.
Simmer sauce ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add pork.
I double the sauce.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar.
Shake well before using.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Make pudding according to package.
Then add all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma bertha carrico's refrigerator rolls
directions: Prepare yeast mixture and add shortening, salt, sugar, mashed potatoes and potato water in large bowl.
Stir until shortening and sugar is dissolved and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in the eggs, then add 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add yeast and blend.
Next add 2 more cups of flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour until dough is soft.
(Do not add more flour than needed.)
Turn on floured board and knead in flour until dough is smooth and can be handled easily. Place in an oiled bowl.
Let rise until double in size.
Knead down and shape into rolls.
Allow to rise double in size.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 50 rolls.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: Combine sugar, coffee and water in pan.
Stir over heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla, brandy and rum.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal. Store in cool, dark place for 2 weeks.
Makes about 2 cups.
Great for gift!
Make about 3 months before giving it away.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool at least 1 hour.
Split cake with a thread and put bottom of split cake back in pan.
Put frosting on bottom portion, then put top of cake on and frost it.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add beans and sprinkle taco seasoning over all.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight (if possible).
Then add cheese, lettuce, dressings, tomatoes and olives, mixing well.
Add crushed taco chips just before serving, mixing well.

title: reese's cups cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in microwave for 45 seconds. Mix graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar with peanut butter/ margarine mixture.
Press dough into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and oil in microwave for 2 minutes.
Pour over dough and refrigerate.

title: mexicali nacho dip
directions: In medium bowl, thoroughly blend nacho cheese recipe soup mix, sour cream and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with tortilla, corn or potato chips.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: crock pot  potatoes
directions: In a crock pot melt margarine.
Add sour cream, soup and onions.
Stir in cooked potatoes.
Cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fig cake
directions: The
cinnamon,	cloves,
nutmeg, salt, soda and vanilla can be cut to 1 teaspoon if not wanted too spicy.

title: granola
directions: Mix salt, oatmeal, wheat germ, nuts and seeds in large casserole or baking pan.
Mix oil, water, vanilla, honey and molasses; pour over dry mixture.
Spread all in 2 or 3 shallow pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring often.
After baking, add raisins and/or chopped dates.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar; beat eggs.
Add vanilla, butter and milk. Mix well.
Bake at 325°.

title: rhubarb cherry jam
directions: Combine rhubarb with sugar and let stand overnight.
The next day cook until tender; stir in pie filling and jello.
Bring to a boil; cool.
Put in jars and refrigerate or freeze.

title: mammaw's potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chess pie(recipe of mrs. r. h. ward, a past president)
directions: Cream butter, sugar, spices, beaten eggs and meal.
Add milk last.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook slowly for 50 minutes, until mixture thickens.
Use whites of eggs for meringue.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple with lime Jell-O.
Mix Cool Whip with cottage cheese.
Add to Jell-O and pineapple.
Add pecans and celery. Refrigerate until jelled.
Serve.

title: tots jello salad
directions: Mix 2 boxes Jell-O in 1 cup hot water; cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in mold or long cake pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: honey crunch cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter.
Add honey, a little at a time; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Mixture will appear to separate.
Gradually add dry ingredients; mix until moistened.
Fold in coconut, chips and cereal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove cookies to cooling rack. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Slowly add milk and water while stirring to avoid lumps.
Heat mixture until hot, but not boiling, stirring often.
Pour into cups and top with marshmallows.
Makes 4 (6-ounce) servings.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Arrange in bottom of large buttered baking dish.
Place chicken or turkey on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Spread over all.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until thoroughly heated through.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well except brown sugar and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar; cream well.
Add pimiento, green pepper, onion and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill, then roll in finely chopped nuts.
Chill again.
Very good!

title: party popcorn
directions: Combine marshmallows and butter in the top of a double boiler; cook over simmering water until marshmallows have melted.
Pour over popped corn and stir to mix well.
Sprinkle gelatin over popcorn and stir to coat each kernel.

title: make ahead muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 cup bran and salt. Let stand to cool. Mix all ingredients together and put in covered dish. Keep refrigerated; lasts up to 2 weeks. Add nuts or fruit as you bake muffins. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Speeds up tasty breakfast or supper!

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add 1/2 cup water in a medium saucepan; cook over low heat until berries are soft. Combine cornstarch and 6 tablespoons water in a small mixing bowl. Stir well.
Add cornstarch mixture to blueberry mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside to cool.

title: fast dessert
directions: Layer fruit in pan.
Sprinkle on cake mix.
Drizzle stick of butter, melted, over fruit and cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake according to cake mix instructions.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
In skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, mustard and salt.
Heat until bubbly.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange half of broccoli.
Top with 1/2 of the eggs, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of the mushroom sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle onions on top and bake 5 minutes more.
Put a few egg slices on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cut yams in halves.
Boil until soft.
Peel and mash.
Toast coconut.
Add butter and other spices to yams.
Mix well.

title: hot tuna salad
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix together tuna, celery, 1 cup croutons, mayonnaise, almonds, onion, lemon juice and salt. Cover.
Heat in microwave for 10 minutes, giving dish 1/4 turn after 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and remaining croutons. Heat for 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Bring milk to boiling point and add marshmallows.
When marshmallows are almost dissolved, take pan off heat and cool mixture.
Add whipped cream, pineapple and cut cherries. Roll crackers and put in bottom of pan.
Save some for top.
Pour pudding mixture on crumbs.
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Decorate with bits of cherries.
Chill.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Chill.
Roll in a ball and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pear honey preserves
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add pears; cover with lid.
Process until finely chopped, not pureed. Measure pears to equal 4 cups.
Combine pears and sugar in a heavy saucepan; bring mixture slowly to a boil and cook, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add pineapple; cook an additional 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch head space; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on bands.
Process jars in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yield: 6 half pints.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons cake mix.

title: single crust apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in open-faced raw crust at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until set and crust is brownish.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine; mix with cracker crumbs and sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pork and sausage tombouile
directions: In a heavy aluminum pot, brown sausage; remove and set aside. Brown pork; remove and set aside. Saute chopped vegetables until soft; add roux, stirring to blend well. Add next 9 ingredients; return to a boil. Place meats back into pot. Simmer on low flame for 4 to 5 hours. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking. Add parsley and onion tops just before serving. Serve over steamed rice or pasta. 24 servings.

title: butternut tostada
directions: Good recipe for people who like Mexican food but can't eat beans.

title: squam scallop pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute garlic in 1/4 cup butter.
Remove and discard garlic.
Saute onion until soft and clear, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add wine; cook 3 minutes.
Add scallops and saute 3 minutes.
Remove scallops with slotted spoon; reserve.
Whisk flour into pan juices and whisk in half and half.
Reduce heat. Cook constantly until thickened and smooth, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Place scallops in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over scallops.
Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter and sprinkle over top.
Cook 15 minutes.
Garnish.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix cream of celery soup with the milk and rice.
Pour into an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Lay lightly salted and peppered chicken in mixture.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 2 hours or until done.

title: pusharotters
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except raisins and nuts) and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and raisins.
Roll into small balls and deep fry
until brown.
Drain on paper towels and dip into icing.

title: mom's best chicken
directions: Cook chicken
in
pot with water, diced celery, carrots and bouillon as
if making soup.
When chicken is well cooked, remove from broth	and
let cool.	Dip cooled chicken (with or without skin) in
beaten
egg
and	then bread crumbs.
Put in frypan of melted butter and fry until browned on each side and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Combine
bread
crumbs
and
light	bread crumbs, onions, 1
1/2 eggs and giblet meat in large mixing bowl. Pour broth over ingredients and mix well.
Put in casserole bowl and put remaining eggs
over	mixture.
Pour	cream of chicken soup over the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a microwavable bowl, add first 3 ingredients.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 5 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add soda (this will foam up).
Stir completely.
Pour onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Spread out as best as possible.
Cool completely.
Break into small pieces.
Do not store in plastic container.
If more than one batch is made at the same time, microwave on High at 4 1/2, 4 1/2 and 2; third batch on High at 4, 4 and 2 minutes.
(Microwave gets hot and peanut brittle would burn if cooked at the first time limit.)

title: broccoli, cheese, rice and chicken casserole
directions: Heat together the water, cheese, margarine, milk and soup. Add the remaining ingredients; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased 2-quart casserole.

title: holiday punch
directions: Add 7-Up at the last minute and garnish with orange slices.

title: rosettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip rosette iron into batter being careful not to cover top of iron.
Fry in hot vegetable oil. Drain rosettes upside down on paper towel.
Yield 40.
Carbohydrate 18 g, protein 5 g, fat 8 g, calories per 2 cookies 32.
Six rosettes = 1/2 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder together. Bring milk with butter to a boil.
Add to the cake mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients except kisses in a large mixing bowl on low speed until dough is firm. Shape into balls by rounded teaspoon. Roll in sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 - 12 minutes at 350. Immediately top with kisses on each. Press firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: turkey chili(low calorie and low sodium)
directions: Brown ground turkey in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Pour off any grease after cooking.
Add chili seasoning.
Mix well.
Add the drained green beans and mix in.
Add the tomato juice (4 cups to start).
Add more if needed.
Simmer on top of stove for approximately 25 minutes.
Season with salt if you wish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Drain excess liquid of salsa. Combine all ingredients, except crackers, in medium bowl. Let stand at least 30 minutes to blend flavors. Serve with Town House crackers.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, eggs, milk, vanilla and cherries. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeats. Mix well. Shape dough into balls and roll in crushed cornflakes.

title: tex mex hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pan-fry ground beef until light brown in skillet; drain fat.
Add onions and pepper; cook until onions are tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients; heat until warm.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: brownies-mexican fudge cake
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar well and add eggs one at a time. Beat.
Add chocolate syrup.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes (approximately) at 350° and cool.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
After boils, lower heat until mixture becomes soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter; do not stir until pan is cool to touch.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Put in buttered platter.

title: marion's homestyle pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Knead on a floured board 10 to 15 times, until no longer sticky.
Cover and let rest for 5 minutes.
Grease and dust cookie sheet with cornmeal.
Roll out dough into a rectangle.
Place in pan and top with favorite sauce, cheese and toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in a bowl.
Combine salt, onions, celery, cloves, whole black peppers, wine vinegar and bay leaves.
Pour over meat; cover and refrigerate for 2 or 3 days, turning meat occasionally. Place meat into large pot; drain marinade over meat.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat until tender.
In a saucepan blend the butter, flour, sugar, some of the liquid from the meat and crumbled gingersnaps.
Stir into the meat, cooking until thickened.
Pour into a hot serving dish. Serve with potato dumplings.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Saute onions in butter; peel and slice potatoes and barely cover with hot water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until mushy.
Stir in soup.
Cut cheese in thin slices and stir until melted.
Stir in milk, more or less depending on consistency desired.

title: pineapple cake surprise
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Set aside and allow cake to cool completely.
Using wooden spoon, poke holes randomly through cake.
Pour can sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Pour crushed pineapple over that.
Using spatula, spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut, then put cherries on top for added color and flavor.

title: fish fillets baked in foil
directions: Cut each fillet into 3 portions.
Place each in center of 8-inch square of buttered, double-duty aluminum foil.
Peel and thinly slice onions and carrots.
Place over fillets.
Melt margarine; pour over each serving.
Dust with pepper, salt and parsley.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Top with cheese.
Fold foil over fish and close all edges.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes in hot oven at 425°.
Open foil and serve.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Separate dough into different batches.
Add chocolate chips, nuts or raisins to give different cookies.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: plum spice cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Add eggs, baby food, food coloring, flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon and nuts. Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy hearty corn chowder
directions: Blend all ingredients and cook over low heat until potatoes and celery are done.
Add water for desired thickness.

title: cottage supper bake
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
In 9-inch square baking dish, arrange hash brown potatoes over bottom and sides.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake 15 minutes.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: angel hair pasta with crab
directions: Boil pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix cream, flour, margarine, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add crab, crumbled.
Reheat until crab is warm.
Add pasta to sauce and mix good.
Serve with salad and wheat rolls.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Chop and cook broccoli until tender. Drain. Set aside. Together melt cheese and margarine until melted and creamy. Spread broccoli evenly in casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture evenly over top. Crumble Ritz crackers over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: dried tomato pasta
directions: Cook the fettucini in boiling, salted water with a little olive oil added.
Meanwhile, soak the sun-dried tomatoes in very hot water to soften.
Slice olives and cut softened tomatoes into 1/2 inch pieces (discard soaking water).
Chop garlic and saute in olive oil in skillet.
Add tomatoes and olives to skillet; toss with garlic, then reduce heat until fettucini is ready.
Crumble Feta cheese.
When done, drain fettucini but do not blanch.
Toss cheese in pan with hot, drained pasta.
Serve on plates with tomato/olive mixture spooned over pasta.
Serve with a nice salad and warm bread.
Serves 2.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Place fruit in bowl; stir in sour cream.
Add marshmallows. Cover and refrigerate, preferably overnight.
Serves 6.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Roll hamburger patties in flour and brown in hot fat.
Place in baking dish and cover with mixture of soup, milk and salt and pepper.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: easy chocolate layered dessert
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: best banana bars
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in the eggs, bananas and vanilla. In separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt. Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture gradually and mix well. Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bars test done with a toothpick. Cool.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well and let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheets for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and sifted dry ingredients, alternately.
Last, add vanilla. Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beth's cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and add rest of ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap in glass bowl and refrigerate for 1 to 3 hours. Drain liquid and serve.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, oleo and peanut butter until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate pieces.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and edges pull away from pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: artichoke dressing
directions: Drain artichoke hearts.
Cut artichoke hearts into slices. Add chopped garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients several hours until all ingredients are tender.
A slow cooker can be used.
Great on chips or oven baked chicken or fish.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown meats, draining fat.
Add onions to meat.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add sugar, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard and seasonings.
Add beans.
Pour mixture into 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Brown shrimp in 1/2 stick margarine.
Brown onion and pepper in 1/2 stick margarine.
Combine onion, pepper, tomatoes, celery, garlic, bouillon and olives; simmer 35 minutes.
Add wine and shrimp; heat thoroughly.
Add rice and garnish with chopped eggs. Serves 5 or 6.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Crush chips.
Layer in bottom of casserole dish.
Stir together the chicken, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except tomato. Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving. When ready to serve, add tomato and toss gently.

title: no peek chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice and liquid together, pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with chicken pieces until most of rice mixture is covered. Sprinkle with dry onion mix.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl for 2 minutes.
Pour into 12 muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine all except bread and butter.
Pour in baking dish. Place bread, cut in strips, on top.
Melt butter and pour on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lorna doones
directions: Mix crushed Lorna Doone cookies with margarine and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Press mixture in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix pineapple, 1 cup confectioners sugar and cream cheese until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over baked cookie crust and chill.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: pagoge
directions: Mix together and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a wok. Serve this with rice and soy sauce.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix milk and egg well.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Wash and dry wieners.
Cook in deep hot fat until golden brown.

title: pork chops made easy
directions: Pour undiluted soup over uncooked pork chops.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice or fettucini.

title: bour-b-que sauce
directions: Warm and use.
Makes approximately 2/3 quart.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute chicken, onion, bell pepper, garlic and chiles.
Add enchilada sauce and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Wrap with tortillas. Lay in baking pan.
Cover with cheese and extra sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cover with cilantro when serving.

title: crock-pot scramble
directions: Throw all the first 6 ingredients in the crock-pot and cook on low setting for 6 hours, give or take an hour or two (depends on how long you'll be away, don't worry, it won't overcook).
Add the remaining ingredients, turn pot up to high for about 30 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Add the two cans of chili.
Slice thin the pepper Jack cheese and layer on top.
Bake in a moderate oven until the cheese melts. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Stir in crackers and peanut butter.
When well blended, drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat potatoes, cream, lemon peel, juice, spices and egg yolk until smooth.
Reserve 1/3 cup coconut; fold remaining coconut into the mixture.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually beat in brown sugar to make a stiff meringue.
Fold into sweet potato mixture.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole; top with reserved coconut and almonds.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes (or until knife blade comes out clean when inserted in center).

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Sprinkle cranberries with diet sweetener and simmer in soda pop for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and drain. Refrigerate before serving.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Line bottom of Dutch oven with seasoned meat.
In large bowl mix all ingredients.
Using soup can fill 1/2 full of water plus 4 tablespoons corn starch.
Add to mixture and season.
Pour over meat in dutch oven.
Cook at 275 degrees for 5 hours.
Make sure the Dutch oven has a tight fitting lid.
Do not open the oven until the 5 hours are up.
Serves 6 people.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and mix in carrots.
Good served hot or well chilled.

title: casserole from old mexico
directions: In a bowl, combine corn, biscuit mix, egg, butter, sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Turn half of batter into well-greased 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with chiles, then with cheese slices. Spread remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sherbet punch
directions: In a punch bowl, dissolve jello with water.
Stir in frozen lemonade and add 3 cups cold water.
Pour in cranberry juice.
Add ice cubes.
Pour ginger ale in slowly.
Scoop out sherbet and add to punch.

title: easy buttermilk rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda; mix well.

In a small saucepan, combine buttermilk, water and shortening; place over low heat until hot. Gradually add the milk mixture to the dry ingredients, stirring to combine, then beat well until very smooth.
Stir in the remaining flour until the mixture comes away from the sides of the bowl.

title: "lovelight" chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar slowly and beat until shiny and stiff peaks.

title: caramel apples
directions: Mix honey and evaporated milk together.
Cook, stirring constantly, to the firm-ball stage or to 255° on a candy thermometer.

title: gooey pie(this pie will delight a child.)
directions: In a double boiler, heat milk, stir in Hershey bars and marshmallows and cook until melted.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with whipped cream.

title: fried turkey breast
directions: Slice turkey breast 1/2 inch across the grain.
Place in large bowl.
Mix egg, buttermilk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over the meat.
Put enough flour in a brown paper bag to coat turkey.
Fry in hot oil 350° until brown (like you fry fish).

title: pinwheel
directions: Boil potato until done.
Mash the potato.
Gradually add powdered sugar to potato.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.

title: six minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add butter, milk, Karo and bring to full boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 6 minutes.
Cool mixture for 15 minutes.
Add flavoring and beat until creamy.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour onto a buttered platter.
Cut when cold.
(Very habit forming.)

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Bake.
While cake is baking, in a saucepan on top of the stove, cook the frosting on low heat.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine (melted); press into 13 x 9-inch buttered dish.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in oleo until tender.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, salt and black pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes. Place mixture in a greased and shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until eggplant is tender.

title: sliced baked potatoes(can be used as a main dish)
directions: Use new potatoes.
Wash and slice thin 3/4 way through.
Put in baking dish and fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter and herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Check with fork to make sure they are soft.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake an additional 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: pecan sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix to make topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and add tuna, mushroom soup, cheese and salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butter pecan oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs, shortening, 1/2 cake mix and water until smooth. Stir in rest of cake mix, nuts and raisins. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheets.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese; add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in flour.
Bake at 325°, starting with a cold oven, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: One hour before serving, cook linguini in 2-quart pan over medium heat.
Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour and gradually add milk, mushrooms and liquid, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese and then chicken.
Add linguini and gently toss.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: original girl scout cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, milk, vanilla and flour which have been sifted with salt and baking powder.
Mix these ingredients well. Chill for about 1 hour. Roll out very thick and cut with 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden. Sprinkle baked cookies with sugar.

title: refreshing salad
directions: Grate the radishes, salt it and let it stand for 1 hour. Squeeze the liquid out of the radishes.
Add chopped hard-boiled eggs, grated cheese, peas and mayonnaise to taste.

title: molasses applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Cut in margarine.
Add molasses, egg and applesauce.
Beat well. Stir in raisins.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out and sprinkle with confectioners sugar or glaze with 1 1/2 tablespoons lemon juice and sugar.

title: john henry
directions: Saute in a skillet the first 4 ingredients in the oil.
Cook the macaroni with salt to taste.
Put sauteed vegetables aside and brown the ground beef in skillet with salt and pepper.
Pour off grease.
Mix vegetables with meat. Add the barbecue sauce, tomato sauce, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Pour water off macaroni.
Put half the macaroni in baking dish.
Spoon half the meat sauce on top of macaroni. Sprinkle with 1 cup grated cheese. Repeat layers of macaroni and meat sauce. Top with 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: creme-de-menthe bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Add flour.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing with cooled spaghetti.
Add bottle of Salad Supreme.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Use sliced Granny Smith apples for dipping.

title: cheese square appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).

title: luau baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from skillet.
Cook onion in fat. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: three bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain all beans.
Mix vegetables in large plastic container.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Put tight lid on container and toss occasionally.
Refrigerate.

title: crabmeat casserole(serves 10)
directions: Mix cream and mayonnaise together.
Add all other ingredients, reserving a little stuffing to sprinkle on top.
Put in buttered casserole and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: meringue for puddings
directions: Beat egg whites until they peak.
Beat in sugar, cornstarch and vanilla.
Beat until very stiff.
Spread on pudding and brown in hot (375°) oven.

title: apricot cheesecake
directions: In a medium bowl combine crushed butter cookies and melted butter.
Press mixture evenly onto bottom and 2 inches up the side of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: rotel green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Pour 1 can into a 2-quart casserole dish. Slice onion into rings.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over the beans. Place 1/2 of the onion on top and sprinkle with half the grated cheese.
Add the second can of green beans and repeat layers of soup mixture, onion and grated cheese.
Top with bacon slices. Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Cook bread crumbs and milk until thick, then add sugar, cocoa, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, egg yolks and raisins.
Fold in whites and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour (until firm in center).

title: sausage and cheese bagels
directions: In skillet, brown sausage; lower the skillet temperature and add cheese. When cheese has melted, remove from stove. Cut bagels in half and lay open in a greased baking dish. Spoon sausage and cheese mixture onto the top of the bagel. Cook in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Combine the flour and seasonings; coat the chicken breasts. Melt the butter in a baking dish.
Place the chicken in the dish, skin side down.
Bake 1 hour at 375°, turning chicken after 30 minutes.

title: jezebel (it's hot!!)
directions: Spread cream cheese on a cracker and garnish with a small amount of Jezebel.
Guaranteed to warm the cockles of your heart!

title: triple strawberry delight
directions: Combine pretzels and butter. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over pretzel layer.
Combine jello and water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour on top of cream cheese layer.
Cool.

title: baked pears
directions: In shallow baking dish, buttered, arrange pear halves, cut sides up.
Dot the pears with butter.
Sprinkle them with dark brown sugar and pour in a mixture of half the pear syrup and an equal amount of wine.
Bake the pears in hot oven (400°) until they are light brown in color.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to juice. Bring to a boil and pour over jello.
Mix well and then add all remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to all together.
Fold in nuts. Bake in greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in baking pan.
Pour dry cake mix over peaches. Chop butter into small pieces and put on top of cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake according to time and temperature specified on cake mix box.

title: party vegetable sandwiches
directions: Combine cheese, salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in vegetables and chill several hours.
Spread on bread and serve.
Yields 2 cups of filling.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Cook sour cream and sugars until it reaches the soft ball stage (220°).
Beat with a spoon until it starts to thicken.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Cut when cooled.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until done and drain.
Mix rice, chopped broccoli, cream of mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz together.
Cook at 350° until done, about 30 or 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the stick of margarine in a baking dish and pour into the other ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Return to the baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour; mix well.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Divide into three parts; roll out as if you were making pie crust.
Cut each circle into 8 sections the shape of a piece of pie.
Roll wide edge into the point (like crescent rolls) and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 3 or more hours. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: apple rolls
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg in a saucepan, stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Stir in butter.
Set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut shortening into flour mixture with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface, roll out to 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread apples over dough and roll up in jelly roll.
Cut 1 inch slices (12). Place cut side down in cake pan.
Pour sugar syrup around slices. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together; chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Pour boiling water over cucumbers and let stand overnight, then pack in jars.

title: finger paint
directions: Heat to boiling.
Sprinkle salt in after mixture starts thickening.
Add food coloring and cool.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape in baking pan or Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except whipped cream.
Let stand 1 hour. Before serving, add whipped cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat beef strips with a mixture of 1 tablespoon flour and salt.
In a skillet, brown beef strips quickly in 2 tablespoons butter (or margarine).
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is crisp-tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove meat and mushrooms from skillet.

title: broccoli slaw salad
directions: Break up noodles with hammer. Mix slaw with chopped green onions. Make a sauce with the sugar, vinegar, oil and 2 chicken flavoring packets inside Ramen noodles. Then add noodles to sauce and coat well. Then add slaw to mixture and stir well. Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours to soften noodles. Before serving, add sunflower seeds.

title: smoked spot
directions: Arrange fillets on smoker grill.
To each, apply pat of butter or margarine.
Add salt, pepper and paprika (for color).
To coals, add hickory or mesquite chips according to smoker directions.
Cook slowly for 15 to 18 minutes or until slightly golden in color.
Serve with hush puppies, salad and corn.
Serves 4.

title: kim's peanut butter cup bars
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, sugar and graham crackers.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over the top.
Cut after 1/2 hour, before completely cool.

title: nutmeg bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with vegetable oil spray. In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and margarine. Add egg substitute and applesauce and beat well. Put remaining ingredients, except buttermilk, in a medium bowl. Sift together twice. Alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk to sugar mixture, beginning and ending with flour, stirring after each addition. Pour batter into loaf pan. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until cake tester or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn bread onto cooling rack.
Serves 16 (1 slice per serving).

title: freezer burgers
directions: Brown beef until red disappears.
Add onions, garlic and celery and saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Freeze.
Reheat and serve on hamburger buns when needed.
Makes 10 cups.
This is good to have in freezer for unexpected company.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and cube.
Combine with next 4 ingredients while potatoes are still warm.
Combine and whisk next 7 ingredients and pour over potatoes and vegetables.
Let sit several hours or overnight, tossing occasionally.
Add mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.

title: tea party loaf
directions: Stir together biscuit mix, rolled oats and sugar.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add to oat mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in chocolate bits, butterscotch bits and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean from center of loaf.
Cool 10 minutes before turning out of pan. Use a 5 x 9 x 3-inch pan.

title: halftime sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Melt cheese.
Combine Ro-Tel with sausage and cheese.
Place in a crock-pot on medium setting and serve with plain Doritos or dip-style Fritos.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream together butter and sugar; add sour cream.
Stir in sifted ingredients.
Chill dough overnight.
Divide in half and roll out on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out shapes.
Bake on ungreased sheets at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Make batter by combining first 5 ingredients.
Melt butter in good size baking pan.
Pour in batter.
Pour fruit and juice on top of batter.
Do not stir!!
Bake at 375° to 400° until done, nicely brown.
This is a group size cobbler.
Work 1/2 recipe for family.
Plenty of juice makes it better.

title: miss mona's meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Add more milk if mixture is too dry.
Place in a loaf pan and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour. About 15 minutes before the meat loaf is done, spoon some tomato sauce over the top.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove shells from cooked eggs.
Cut eggs in half crosswise. Remove yolk.
Mash yolk with fork.
Add salt, mayonnaise, ketchup, mustard and mashed yolk; stir.
Refill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish with paprika.

title: quick zucchini cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cake mix, eggs, oil, vanilla and cinnamon for 6 to 7 minutes.
Fold in zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick at 40 minutes.
Invert onto cake plate.

title: mexican-corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into an oven-safe casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until warm throughout.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and let cool, then tear into small pieces and set aside.
While chicken is boiling also, in a different pot, cut up broccoli cuts (if they are in very large pieces) and let steam or boil until tender but not falling to pieces.
Drain broccoli and set aside.

title: squash patties
directions: Place
grated squash and onion in a colander.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let sit over sink until all moisture is gone.
Add flour, corn
meal,
pepper,
cheese
and
egg mix.
Form into patties or balls and fry until browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add seasoning, sauce and paste; simmer for 25 minutes.
Boil 6 noodles.
Mix 4 eggs and cottage cheese.

In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 meat, 3 noodles, all cottage cheese, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and repeat 1/3 meat and 3 noodles. End with meat, rest of Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan and mushrooms. Bake 30 minutes at 350°; cool 15 minutes.

title: casserole kielbasa
directions: Cook kielbasa slightly; cut into slices about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick, and place in crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce and pineapple. Simmer for several hours.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and shortening; melt over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and salt. Beat in sugar alternately with milk.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix
the mixed vegetables, mushroom soup, chicken soup, chicken broth, onion,
salt and pepper to taste altogether and pour over some chunked,
boiled
chicken in a 9 x 13-inch size pan.
Mix the flour,
milk	and melted butter.
Pour on top of mixture. Do not stir in.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: scampi
directions: In large frypan, saute onion in 1/2 cup margarine until tender. Transfer to large bowl.
Add shrimp, olive oil, garlic, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place shrimp in a large, shallow baking pan, making sure you add any remaining liquid.
Broil 5 minutes, 6-inches from heat.
Turn and broil another 5 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium sized bowl, combine pancake mix, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken breasts in the mixture a few at a time to coat well.
Place chicken in a shallow 3-quart baking dish, overlapping slightly if necessary.
Combine mushroom soup, onion soup mix and milk in a small bowl and blend until smooth. Pour over chicken.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour. Remove foil and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes longer.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Place in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hazel's 6 week muffins
directions: Mix as named.
Let mix set in refrigerator overnight.
Pour in muffin tin lined with muffin liners or spray with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: mom's potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onions alternately (onions keep potatoes white).
Add egg yolks and flour to potatoes.
In a separate dish, beat egg whites until fluffy.
Fold into potato batter.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown on both sides.
You may top with sour cream, jelly, cream cheese or applesauce.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Let all ingredients simmer; meanwhile, prepare meat balls. Add meat balls to sauce and cook for one hour.
Add oregano if desired and water if necessary.
Meat balls must be turned often. Cover pot 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook mixture until clear.
Add jello.
Mix well and cool slightly.
Pour over berries.
Pour into shell.
Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes, still stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oatmeal; stir until oatmeal is covered.
Spoon onto aluminum foil.
Let harden.

title: popcorn garland
directions: String popcorn onto thread.
Every so often, add a bead. Drape garland around tree and enjoy the beauty.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Lightly butter muffin tins.
Stir together flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine milk, butter, egg and vanilla.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture. Add the milk mixture and stir to combine.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon in cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes (until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean) at 400°.
Remove to
a wire rack and cool 5 minutes.
Remove from tins.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put in loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake for 90 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil.
Cool.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Put in containers. Keeps in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve piping hot.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil with sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add carrots.
Place in greased pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or more.
I prefer to cook until just done enough to turn out of pan.
Cool; ice with Nut Icing.

title: quick pepper steak
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil; brown beef and remove.
Add peppers and onion (cut into strips) and garlic powder.
Cook over medium heat until crisp.
Add gravy and Worcestershire; return beef to pan.
Heat; serve over rice.

title: mary vickers(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (200°C).
Remove crust from bread and spread each slice with a mixture of all other ingredients.
Cut into strips or any other desired shape.
If desired, freeze on a baking sheet, place in a freezer bag and store in freezer until needed.
To serve, bake for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: cheesy ham bake
directions: Combine eggs, milk, mustard and seasoning.
Stir in macaroni, one cup cheese, ham, onion and pimento.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Sprinkle remainder of cheese over top of casserole before baking.)

title: pierogi
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add flour as necessary just enough so dough can be rolled.
Cut into circles with glass or cup.
Fill with mashed potatoes, meat, cheese, fruit or sauerkraut.
Fill half circle with filling, fold over and press edges together with fork to seal.
Drop into boiling water for a couple of minutes. Remove with slotted spoon.
Serve with melted butter and sauteed onions.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and spaghetti mix.
Bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Layer ground beef on bottom, lasagna noodles and cheese (be sure to end up with meat on top).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 250°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese while still hot.

title: blue ridge sweet red pepper relish
directions: Core, seed and chop red peppers medium - coarse.
Peel and chop onions medium - coarse.
Peel, core and chop apples, medium coarse. Place vegetables and apples in large enamel or stainless steel pot. Pour in just enough of the boiling water to cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine vinegar, cold water, sugar and salt in medium-sized enamel pan.
Bring to boiling; stir to dissolve sugar. Lower heat, simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Drain vegetable-apple mixture well.
Return to same pot.
Pour in vinegar mixture.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Put in pint jars after cooking thoroughly and seal (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Eat on hot dogs and hamburgers. Also on green beans.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With sharp knife cut meat across grain into thin strips. Combine soy sauce and garlic.
Add beef and set aside.
Prepare vegetables.
Heat oil; add beef and brown.
Cook until tender (30 to 40 minutes) over low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables. Cook about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to meat and vegetables.
Stir until thick and add cut up tomatoes just before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in 9-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and spread on top of peaches. When using fresh peaches, sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with milk or ice cream.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange layer of potatoes in greased casserole.
Cover with some onion, parsley, bacon bits and cheese.
Sprinkle some of the combined flour, salt and pepper on top.
Repeat layers until all is used.
Melt butter in milk and pour it over.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: jam squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves in large mixing bowl; beat at low speed on electric mixer until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 2 cups mixture; press remaining onto bottom of greased 13x9-inch baking pan. Spread preserves evenly over base; sprinkle with reserved mixture. Bake in preheated hot oven (400F) 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool; cut into squares. Makes 13x9-inch pan of squares.

title: blueberry clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and shortening and place pan over hot water.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Gently fold in blueberries until well coated with chocolate.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto wax paper.
Chill until chocolate is set.
Makes about 3 dozen.
May be kept at room temperature up to one hour.

title: hanky panky
directions: Cook meat separately until done.
Drain well.
Combine meat and add cheese.
Cook on low until melted, 3 or 4 minutes.
Spread on cocktail ryes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain grease.
Drain juice from canned vegetables.
Pour all ingredients into a 10-quart stockpot and boil gently for 1 hour.
Yields 6 quarts of soup.

title: cold german potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes. After potatoes are cooked and cooled, peel and slice. Add to dressing and stir slightly. Let stand for at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put 1/2 of mixture into another bowl.
Layer 1/2 of Cheddar and Monterey Jack on top, then add the rest of the mixture and top with the remaining Cheddar and Monterey Jack.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet.
Fry chicken until brown.
Drain and place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about
1 hour or until chicken is done. Baste occasionally.

title: beer marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over meat, cover and refrigerate.
This makes meat tender.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cook chicken breast in water and cover with 1 bay leaf for 30 minutes or until juices run clear.
Cool; remove skin.
Cut in bite-size pieces. Combine noodles, chicken, celery, pepper, olives, cheese, onions and dressing.
Serve warm or cold.

title: homemade chocolate frosting
directions: Cook over medium heat sugar, milk and marshmallows.
Pour over margarine, nuts and chocolate chips.
Stir while pouring.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix and put into 9x13 ungreased pan.
Sprinkle regular size white cake mix over top.
Melt 3/4 c. butter and pour over dry cake mix.
Bake 305° for 1 hour.

title: skewered grilled potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and water in a 2-quart bowl.
Cover; microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Marinate 1 hour.
Grill until brown.

title: easy pickle recipe
directions: Mix the salt, celery seed, sugar and white vinegar together and heat until salt and sugar are dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers, onions and pepper.
Put in jar and store in refrigerator.
These pickles will keep a long time and are delicious.

title: pie crust
directions: Put flour in bowl and mix in salt.
Mix oil and milk together and stir into flour to make dough.
Roll out dough between 2 sheets of plastic.
Don't touch dough.
This is for a single crust.
Double amount for double crust.

title: arlene's apple crumb pie
directions: Combine ingredients and turn into a 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, making two layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut with whipped topping. Spread between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in airtight container and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days to "ripen." Delicious.

title: rice krispie candy
directions: Combine the first four ingredients in iron skillet; stir with wooden spoon.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.

title: salad
directions: Cream together all ingredients, adding marshmallows last. Cool and serve.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef and onions in skillet until brown.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit tart(dieter's recipe)
directions: Preparation Time: 45 minutes.
No cholesterol (153 calories).

title: lemon torte
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk and milk, then flour and baking powder sifted together.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° in a shallow greased pan.

title: wonder salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix all together and drain overnight.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and milk; pour into the baking dish.
Peel and slice peaches; arrange over batter.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup sugar over peaches.
Pour water over peaches.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: pecan ice cream
directions: Beat the following until fluffy:
brown sugar, white granulated sugar and eggs.
Mix these and add in order:
evaporated milk, pudding, vanilla and pecans.
Use milk to fill container.

title: pinto beans(old timey)
directions: Pick any foreign object from beans.
Wash and place in 2 1/2-quart utensil with a cover.
Cover about 1/4-inch above beans with cold water.
Bring to full boil for approximately 1 minute. Drain off hot water through colander.
Cover beans with hot water again about 1/4-inch above bean level.
Add salt and oil.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
It may be necessary to add more hot water while cooking.
When beans are tender and well done, add sugar or molasses, preferably molasses.
More water may be added if soupy beans are desired.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes (enough to fill a 12 x 9-inch baking dish) and boil until tender.
Layer potatoes and mixture into baking dish. Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble. To bacon drippings add onions, brown sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt, and vinegar. Heat for 20 minutes. Add all beans and bacon, put in casserole dish and cover. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Drain fat, except 1 tablespoon. Crumble bacon.
Add onion, celery, green peppers, garlic, tomatoes, liquid smoke, chicken broth, vinegar, sugar, bay leaf, pepper, peas and shrimp.
Cook over medium heat until shrimp is done.
Put over rice and eat.

title: fancy cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and okra gumbo
directions: Heat 1 teaspoon oil in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add okra and cook, stirring until beginning to brown, 10 minutes. Transfer to medium bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon oil to skillet.
Pat chicken dry on paper towel; sprinkle with salt.
Cook, stirring over medium-high heat until beginning to brown, 5 minutes.
Add to bowl with okra.
Add remaining oil to skillet and reduce heat to medium.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; cook, stirring until onion is soft, 10 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook until browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic and cook 30 seconds.
Transfer mixture to Dutch oven; stir in remaining ingredients and cook for 10 minutes, or until shrimp are opaque.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve over rice.

title: fried chicken with hot cranberry sauce
directions: Cut up broilers.
Season with 2 teaspoons of salt, pepper and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of flour.
Sift remaining flour, salt and baking powder into a bowl.
Beat in egg and water.
Dip chicken pieces in this batter, coating them thoroughly.
Heat the fat to 370° and fry chicken a few pieces at a time.
Drain and place in baking dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover for last 10 minutes.
Combine cranberries and applesauce and heat in saucepan.
Serve with chicken.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil together until it forms a soft ball. Brown one cup of sugar and add to mixture. Add one stick of butter. Beat well and spread.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix orange jello, cottage cheese and drained pineapple.
Place in 6 x 9-inch dish.
Place mandarin oranges on top.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: seafood fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to directions.
Saute the peeled shrimp and scallops in a little butter until done, about 3 minutes depending on size of scallops; set aside and keep warm.
Add the white wine, garlic, salt and pepper to saute pan.
Cook 1 minute. Add the oregano, basil and thyme along with cream; bring to a boil.
Simmer for a few minutes until it reduces by half.
Turn down temperature; add Parmesan and fettuccine.
Put seafood on top.
Serves 1.

title: potato bake
directions: Let potatoes thaw (about 1/2 hour). Mix potatoes, chicken soup, sour cream, onion, Cheddar cheese and 1 stick melted oleo; salt and pepper. Put into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle melted oleo over it (3 tablespoons). Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1-1/2-inch pie plate. Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion onto plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute by hand. Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 35-40 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Makes 6 generous slices.

title: fried cabbage patties
directions: Boil cabbage until
slightly cooked.
Drain water; peel leaves.
Take several leaves in
hand and squeeze into a small patty.
Make as many patties as desired.
Beat eggs in a bowl. Mix Romano cheese and seasoned Italian bread crumbs in another bowl. Dip patties in the
egg
bowl,
then remove patties and mix with bread crumbs.
Place
patties
in
pan
and fry until golden brown.

title: mary's pot roast
directions: Rub roast with French dressing.
Let stand covered in refrigerator overnight.
Roll in flour.
Brown in oil in large pot. Cover with lid.
Turn to lowest setting of eye of stove and cook about 4 hours or until tender.

title: chocolate ricotta cake
directions: Mix all together with mixer on medium.
See the recipe for the crust to follow.
Bake in a 10-inch glass pie plate at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls. Dip in sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Blend in milk, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan with Pam vegetable cooking spray and dust with flour.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except raisins and nuts, at low speed until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: dairy noodle kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain and cool.
Mix together beaten egg whites, cottage cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla, raisins and melted margarine; add cooked noodles.
Pour half of the mixture into a well-greased baking dish.
Place a few dots of margarine on this layer.
Put the rest of the mixture into baking dish.
Top with crumbled graham crackers or breadcrumb mixture.
Dot with more margarine.
