Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (or, if prepared ahead of time, bake for 30 minutes, then 15 minutes to reheat).

title: puppy chow(kids love it!)
directions: Microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Stir in vanilla.

title: candy apple delight
directions: Combine whipped topping and pineapple in a bowl.
Chop apples, candy bars and peanuts and fold into whipped topping mixture. Yields 7 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake about 40 minutes at 300°.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Set aside.
Beat eggs slightly in a large bowl. Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients. Stir only until moist.
Spoon into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix linguini and dressing together.
Chill overnight in refrigerator, then add remaining vegetables and seasoning.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix cocoa and flour and add to first mixture.
Add milk and vanilla. Pour into pie shell and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350° until set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together
except for 1/2 of the cheese. Bake at 325° for 1
hour.
Top
with remaining cheese near end of baking.

title: "stewp"(not stew, not soup!)
directions: Bring to boil and cook 1 hour or so.
The more vegies, the better.
May add noodles.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and dice artichoke hearts.
Add the mayo, cheese and garlic powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in a shallow pan and bake until brown and bubbly.
Serve hot on sliced French bread.
Enjoy!

title: lemon shortbread squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients except almonds.
Beat until dough is smooth and comes clean from side of bowl and gathers into ball.
With lightly floured fingers press dough evenly over bottom of 9-inch square pan (ungreased). Sprinkle almonds on top and press gently into dough.
Using sharp knife, score into 16 small squares and prick each square twice with fork.
Bake until dough is barley colored and almonds are lightly toasted, about 20 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes and cut squares all the way through.

title: barbeque sauce
directions: Shake all ingredients in a jar.
Pour sauce over meat (pork chops are especially good).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: val's beef and mac
directions: Add all ingredients except mac.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add mac and serve.

title: peppermint brittle
directions: Crush peppermints until fine.
Melt chocolate in microwave 1 minute then stir.
Repeat until chocolate is fully melted.
Mix in peppermints.
Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool. Break up and serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Add broth and broccoli.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Beat together pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
This is good for about a week kept in refrigerator on cake.

title: southern seafood bake
directions: Combine eggs with 1/4 cup scallop liquid in bowl; mix well. Saute onion in butter in skillet until brown.
Add with remaining ingredients to egg mixture; mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: holiday baked corn
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in well-buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: chili
directions: Cook pinto beans on low heat
with salt for 4 to 6 hours. Check every hour, add water, if necessary.
Brown hamburger or deer and spoon off grease.
Replace half grease with cooking oil and onion and salt to taste.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Sift flour, spices, baking powder and soda.
Set aside.
In another bowl, blend sugar and oil, add eggs.
Stir in pumpkin and add dry ingredients.
Pour into an ungreased tube-center pan, lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan.
May be frozen.
Can be baked in 3 loaf pans about 1 hour instead.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Mix spinach, cream cheese, 1/2 cup of butter and lemon juice.
Grease bottom of casserole.
Layer sliced artichokes.
Cover with spinach mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot generously with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
This is especially attractive if served over a thick sliced tomato, allowing some of the tomato to show.

title: garden zucchini pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine 1 egg, onion and Parmesan cheese; stir in potatoes.
Transfer potato mixture to a 9-inch pie plate or a 10-inch quiche dish.
Pat the mixture in the bottom and up the sides of the dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly on a wire rack. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook zucchini and garlic in hot margarine or butter until zucchini is crisp-tender; cool slightly.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of melted butter,
hot
sauce
and vinegar; put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with dry
Ranch dressing mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well before serving. Makes 1 1/4 cups of dressing. Especially good over avocado and grapefruit.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in tube pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: batter for onion rings or fish
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with whisk.
Dip onion rings, haddock pieces, shrimp or scallops and deep fry or pan fry in at least two inches of oil.
For superb onion rings, use sweet Vidalia onions.
Once fried place on paper towels to drain excess oil.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls to rectangle on cookie sheet.
Pinch dough together at seams.
Bake at 350° for 10 min. or until lightly brown.
Mix mayo, dressing, and cream cheese together. Let crescent rolls cool before spreading mixture on top of baked rolls.
Sprinkle shredded veggies on top, and sprinkle finely grated cheddar cheese on top of veggies before serving.
Cut into squares.
This may be made a day ahead.
Vegetables will stay fresh.

title: idiot rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients well.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix creamed shortening, sugar, eggs, flour and ginger and slowly add water.
Add molasses.
Bake at 350° until it's done.

title: italian rice cake
directions: Cook rice in milk at a low simmer until milk is absorbed and rice is tender.
Cool to room temperature for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: buckeyes(peanut butter balls)
directions: In large bowl, work together the softened margarine, peanut butter and sifted confectioners sugar.
Knead it until like clay. Roll mixture into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls in melted chocolate mixture.
Set on waxed paper to dry.
Makes almost 200 balls.

title: caramel fried ice cream
directions: Using a 1/2 cup ice cream scoop, place 8 scoops of ice cream on a baking sheet. Cover and freeze for 2 hours or until firm.

title: raw cranberry sauce
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice; mix well. Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Pick over salmon carefully.
Reserve liquid for sauce.
Mix next 7 ingredients.
Add salmon. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into buttered mold.
Steam by setting in pan of boiling water at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.
Serve with sauce.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Spread coconut, then nuts in bottom of pan.
Add cake mix (prepared according to directions on box).
Melt margarine, mix with cream cheese and add powdered sugar.
Spread mixture on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light luscious lime salad
directions: Heat diet Sprite.
Mix with cream cheese until dissolved. Strain.
Mix together jello and crushed pineapple.
Add Sprite, cheese mixture and pecans.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Soak rice overnight.
Rinse well and mix with cheese, mushrooms, olives and onions.
Add 1/2 cup hot water and butter. Add tomatoes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, syrup and butter 5 minutes.
Add salt and baking soda.
Pour over 6 quarts popcorn.
Put in roasting pan; put in oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Place in a casserole dish and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: double pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco until crumbly.
Add water and mix.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Let cool.
Stir in other ingredients.
Spread batter in 15 x 10-inch pan and bake at 350° about 45 minutes. While hot, spread 13 ounce jar marshmallow cream on top.
After cake cools, top with:

title: rebecca's chicken corn chowder
directions: Cook chicken breasts with the can of chicken broth in the crock-pot until tender.
(Can put frozen breasts in the crock pot in the morning and cook on low all day.)
Put the first 5 ingredients into a large pan then add the cut up cooked chicken and broth.
Heat through.
Garnish with scallions and shredded cheese.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stock.
Add stock to make sauce desired consistency.

title: georgine's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin and wash chicken breasts and lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Lay cheese slices over the top of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk and pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with thyme or other chicken seasonings.
Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm stuffing generously to completely cover the top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour.

title: corn dogs
directions: Pat frankfurters dry with paper towels.
If desired, insert a wooden skewer into one end of each frankfurter.
Set aside.

title: lemon carrots
directions: Combine carrots, water, sugar and salt in heavy pan.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat until water has evaporated, about 20 minutes.
Add margarine, lemon juice and lemon peel; stir until margarine is melted.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add shortening.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir just to moisten.
Cook on hot griddle or skillet.

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Bring milk and butter to scald (do not boil). Remove from heat and add to bread that has been torn into pieces. Make sure bread is soaked. Add sugar and cinnamon, beat 2 eggs and add to mixture. Raisins may be added (optional).

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put pineapple in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese. Sprinkle over pineapple.
Mix Ritz and butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or hot and bubbly.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 by 13 in. pan.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 min.
Orange Glaze:
Mix 1 c. pwd. sugar with enough orange juice to thin.
Spread over bars.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Place chops in shallow baking dish.
Arrange onions and peppers on top.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 375° covered 1 hour or until chops are tender. Serve with hot rice.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Combine Butterfingers, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand.
Put in ice cream freezer; finish filling with chocolate milk.
When freezer stops, ice cream is ready.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour in ice cream freezer.
Fill milk to line.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Put in pie crust.
Cover with second crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with the eggs.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until real fluffy.
Alternate flour and
eggs, beating well between each addition.
Bake in well greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: bean casserole
directions: Quarter tortillas. Cook hamburger meat and onion in skillet until done (drain grease). First layer, tortilla and put hamburger mixture next (do about 3 layers). Then next layer,

Ranch style beans. Next layer, put cream-style soup first in bowl with maybe 2 tablespoons water so you can spread easier. Next layer, Ro-Tel on top. Then cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts on top, around 30 minutes.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger and onion.
Cook macaroni and drain. Add all ingredients together until warmed.

title: butternut-apple crisp
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and salt.
Add sliced squash and apple slices, tossing gently to coat.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 7-inch baking pan.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of oleo and blend with 2 cups of graham cracker crumbs.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with this mixture.
Beat for 15 minutes eggs, 2 sticks oleo and powdered sugar.
Spread over crumbs.
Slice the bananas over this mixture.
Spread drained pineapple on top.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Place pecans and cherries on top.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and set aside.
Mix soup, eggs, onion and mayonnaise.
Add broccoli.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with cheese, pecans and bread crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Add equal amounts of jelly and chili sauce.
Pour above ingredients into crock-pot.
Make meat balls small and semi-cook them.
Add meat balls to sauce in the crock-pot and simmer until meat balls are done.

title: chicken and rice "one dish"
directions: Put rice in bottom of double roaster pan.
Put in chicken parts.
Pour over Lipton onion soup (1 package makes 3 cups; see directions).
Pour in the
cream of chicken or cream of mushroom soup (not diluted).
Cook in oven for one hour at 350°.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; cook onions.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: melt-in-your-mouth cranberry pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cranberries over bottom. Sprinkle with sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually and beat until well mixed.
Add flour, melted butter and melted shortening to egg-sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Pour over top of cranberries.
Bake at 325° until crust is golden brown, about 60 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and place into a well-greased and floured 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Beat at 350° for 1 hour or more. Cool well.

title: kielbasa with sauce
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1/2-inch
slices and place on cookie sheet. Cook 10 minutes to remove some fat.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over kielbasa.
Cook 10 minutes or until browned.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 to 40 minutes (longer if necessary).
Make sure center is done.

title: cocktail wiener quickies
directions: Roll wieners in ketchup, then in crumbs.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt all ingredients in the top of a double boiler.
Place over simmering water.
This takes about 1 hour.
Serve.
Keep caramel sauce warm by covering it on top of double boiler, placed over simmering water.
If sauce becomes too thick, add a small amount of water.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients in 8 x 11 dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until center is done.

title: holiday red punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Enjoy for Holiday!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in thin slices.
Cook and stir mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, brown meat on both sides.
Set aside 1/3 cup of comsomme.
Stir remaining consomme, catsup, garlic and salt in skillet with meat. Blend 1/3 cup consomme and flour.
Stir in meat, etc.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Heat to boiling.
Stirring constantly, about one minute.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: taco dip
directions: Shred hamburg and sausage in a large frypan.
Cook until both have browned.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in chili powder; mix well.
Add in both cans of soup; mix well.
Pour mixture into 9-inch pie plate.
Spread shredded cheese over entire mixture. Pour taco sauce over cheese, trying to make sure all the cheese is covered.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let cool for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour sour cream in the middle of mixture and spread covering only the center area.
Spread tomato, scallions and black olives.
Spread evenly around outer edge of dip.
Ready to serve.
Dip nacho chips in dip and enjoy.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour sheet cake pan (or spray with Pam). Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter together. The batter will be very thick.
Pat into cake pan.
Mix the sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese in another bowl.
Pour over first layer. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until done.
(Do not cook until it is very hard.)

title: pollo y tortilla casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in foil.
Bake at 400° until tender.
Remove bones and cut into pieces.
Mix together soup, milk, onion and tomatoes.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of juice from chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares and place in a layer in bottom of baking dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and drain off water.
Add butter while hot.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Add more stuffing crumbs.
Cook at 350° until crumbs are browned lightly.

title: caramel-walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (350° for glass baking pan).
Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients, except berries. Beat with mixer until smooth and well blended.
Batter will be very thick.
Gently fold in berries.
Spread evenly in pan and prepare topping.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle in 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt.
Pat meat mixture into medium casserole dish.
Put in can green beans (drained).
Spread undiluted tomato soup over beans.
Beat egg into mashed potatoes. Spread potatoes over top of casserole, making edges touch sides of dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican corn
directions: Saute onion in hot oil until golden yellow.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add onion.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: *Or cook 2 (9 ounce) packages of corn according to directions.

title: fish in sour cream
directions: Coat the fish fillets with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.

Place melted butter into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange fish fillets, side by side, and pour buttermilk over fish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until fish is tender and almost all milk has been absorbed. Cover with 3/4 cup thick sour cream and 1 cup buttered bread crumbs on top. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes longer until crumbs are browned.

title: "reese's" peanut butter bars (no bake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Stir with spoon.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: golden chocolate cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake and pudding mix, oil, water and eggs.
Beat on low speed for about 30
seconds or until moistened. Beat 2 minutes on high; blend in sour cream.
Stir in candy bars, chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes before removing.

title: chicken or turkey salad for sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve on sandwiches.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in dish. Stir together soup, broth and pepper in mixing bowl, then pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine baking mix, milk and butter in separate bowl. Stir until smooth.
Pour flour mixture over ingredients in baking dish. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, potato chops and almonds.
Place in large casserole top with the last three ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli - cauliflower
directions: Mix and marinate at least 3 hours - refrigerate.
8 -10 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: corned beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Arrange in layers in large casserole.
Pour milk over top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Recipe may be halved.

title: pizza dip
directions: Press cream cheese in bottom of 9-inch glass pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over cream cheese and layer other ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot as dip for corn chips.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form or cut with cookie shapes on lightly floured surface. This is a fun activity.
Have children wash hands. Give them adequate clean work space.
They will have fun and enjoy eating this snack.

title: applepancakes, apfelpfannkuchen
directions: Sift together flour, 2 tsp. sugar and salt. Beat eggs and milk together. Gradually add flour mixture, beat until smooth. Saute apples in 1/4 c. butter until tender. Mix 2 tbsp. sugar and cinnamon together; toss with apples. Melt 2 tbsp. butter in 6 inch deep fry pan. Pour in the batter to depth of 1/4 inch. When set, place 1/4 of apples on top; cover with more batter. Fry pancake until lightly browned on both sides.

title: cheese asparagus rolls
directions: Remove crusts from bread, roll.
Blend next 3 ingredients. Spread on each slice.
Cook asparagus.
Put 1 asparagus on each slice and wrap or roll.
Use toothpick to secure if necessary. Dip in 1/2 pound melted butter.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer as needed.
Slice in thirds and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn once.

title: pecan patties
directions: Mix together.
Fry as patties or balls.
Stew in undiluted tomato soup on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 300° for about 2 hours or until done.
Remove from oven and let cool about 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice off top of potato, scoop out insides and put in large bowl.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, chives, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mash well, adding milk if necessary.
Stuff back into potato shell and bake about 30 to 45 minutes.
You can add slice of cheese on top.
Use chives and parsley to your taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine broccoli, soup, cheese, mayonnaise, onion and eggs; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over mixture. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Cream the margarine, 1 1/2 cups granulated sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and blend thoroughly again. Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.

In another bowl, combine the 3 tablespoons sugar with the cinnamon. Roll each ball in this mixture and place on ungreased cookie sheet, allowing at least 2-inches between each ball. Bake in a 400° oven for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: frosty pink punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and pineapple juice in a very large pitcher.
Cover and put in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Add the ginger ale.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 29 minutes or longer if needed.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook and peel beets and pack in hot jars.
Cover with syrup. Seal.

title: rice salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine rice, onion, tomato, spring onion and cucumbers.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips or cornflake crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: apricot glazed carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, combine carrots and 3/4 cup water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until carrots are tender. Drain. Add salt and apricot preserves; stir to coat. Cook over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: staci's old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; then slowly add milk. Add egg yolks, reserving the egg whites for meringue. Cook over medium-high heat until thick. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, butter and bananas. Pour pudding mixture over vanilla wafers.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Mix other ingredients alternately with sour cream. Grease 8 or 9-inch tube pan.
Layer batter and cranberry sauce. Swirl cranberry sauce with a spoon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: hot water cake
directions: Mix sugar, molasses and egg.
Add Crisco and flour; stir well. Add remaining ingredients.
Batter will be thin after adding in hot water.
Mix with a mixer for 1 to 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
You can double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in hot water; mix well.
Add crushed pineapple and ice cream.
Stir until ice cream is melted.
Chill 10 minutes and serve.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage with pepper and onion; drain. Add tomato sauce, garlic and Parmesan cheese; simmer for 10 minutes.
Cut bread in 1/2; scoop out some of middle.
Put two bread halves side by side on a large cookie sheet.
Layer on sauce; sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients except sesame seed. Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch. Sprinkle seed over batter.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: indian chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, dark brown sugar, garlic powder, water, ginger and cider vinegar.
Marinate chicken in these ingredients overnight.

title: purple passion
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add sugar and mix with mixer until well blended. Add pineapple, well drained, and mix by hand. Add well drained cherries and stir all together. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: sugar-free lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup
hot water.
Add gradually to cream cheese; mix.
Add pineapple and juice.
Stir in pecans.
Chill. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Combine tapioca, Jell-O and pudding mix with hot water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Let cool completely.
Fold in whipped topping and drained mandarin oranges.
Fold into a 9 x 9-inch pan and chill until set.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa & salt. Add 1 egg at a time, mixing in between eggs. Mix well. Add milk, butter, vanilla & coconut flavoring. Mix well. Pour into pie crusts. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter and stir in the flour until smooth.
Add the milk gradually; stir continuously. Cook until thickened and add salt and pepper.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat well at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Reduce speed and add flour and cream alternately.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° in a well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes (or more).
Serves about 18.

title: pecan and raisin pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, then spices and vinegar.
Add whipped egg whites.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave chicken broccoli bake
directions: Roll chicken pieces in flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Heat browning dish on Full power for 5 minutes.
Add oil and chicken to dish.
Microwave on Full power for 2 minutes on each side.
Place lightly browned chicken pieces in shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining flour over chicken. Combine soup, turmeric, milk and cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Place broccoli and water in dish. Cover and microwave on Full power for 6 minutes.
Drain, then arrange broccoli in single layer in casserole dish.
Add corn and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese to chicken liquid.
Spoon mixture over broccoli and arrange chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cut up in medium pieces; set aside. Mix egg, mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese and onion together and pour over chopped broccoli.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs, then pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mix a little at a time, alternating with water until mixed.
Pour into 3 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber-shrimp salad
directions: Score cucumbers; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in bowl. Add shrimp.
Combine remaining ingredients except lettuce and nuts in a jar with tight-fitting lid.
Shake well.
Pour over shrimp and cucumber slices; toss.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, add almonds.
Use slotted spoon to drain salad and transfer to lettuce-lined plates.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cook 5 hours in crock-pot on low heat.

title: louise's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Set in freezer for 45 minutes.
Dip balls in teaspoon and put on greased cookie sheet.
Space out.
Bake for 7 minutes at 325°.

title: fried chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, seasoned salt and pepper.
Wash chicken pieces and pat dry with paper towels.
Place chicken pieces, a few at a time, in flour mixture.
Seal bag and shake to coat.
In large skillet pour 1/2 inch oil.
Heat oil and brown chicken a few pieces at a time.
Remove to baking dish.
When all chicken is browned, bake chicken, covered, in 250° oven 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear when tested with fork.
For crispy skin uncover during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: 30 day cole slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the salad oil, sugar, salt, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage, green pepper, onion and carrot mixture.
Mix and place in refrigerator up to 30 days.
Always crisp.
Let stand at least 24 hours before serving.

title: sky high biscuits
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, sugar and cream of tartar. Cut in the margarine until the mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Add the egg and milk, stirring quickly.
Knead lightly on floured wax paper.
Roll or pat gently; cut into biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake in 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Very good with bacon and scrambled eggs for breakfast.

title: old time cherry cobbler
directions: Heat cherries to boiling; stir in margarine.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Combine Bisquick and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add milk and melted margarine.
Beat by hand.
Spoon over hot cherries.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Put in angel food cake pan with bottom of pan greased.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheddar soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Combine carrots, celery and onions in a medium saucepan; add broth.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, until vegetables are done.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Scrub potatoes and carrots and cut into serving pieces.
Wrap in heavy aluminum foil and pour cream of mushroom soup over all.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put bread crumbs in large bowl.
Add sweet milk and ground beef.
Beat eggs and add to meat.
Add salt, pepper, sage and onion.
Form into loaf.

title: festive make-ahead pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, then rinse in cold water and drain.
Toss with oil to prevent shells from sticking.
Mix next 6 ingredients in a small bowl until thoroughly blended.
Put lettuce in one layer in a 3-quart bowl (preferably clear glass to show layers).
Top with cooled macaroni, then egg slices.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Add layers of the ham, peas and cheese.
Spread dressing carefully over the top to bowl's edge.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just at serving time.

title: party crab bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and onions.
Arrange half of macaroni in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole.
Dip half of cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls over macaroni.
Spread to cover.
Top with half of crabmeat.
Repeat these layers.
Top crabmeat with sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for approximately 1 hour in 450° oven.
Slice lengthwise and scoop out potato pulp.
Mash potato pulp well.
Add while potato is hot; corned beef hash, onion, salt, pepper, milk and cheese.
Mix well and restuff potatoes.
Bake until hot or microwave for approximately 3 minutes.
(May freeze and cook individually as needed.)

title: california oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dip the chicken pieces in melted butter, then shake them in a paper bag containing the garlic powder, paprika, thyme, salt and crumbs or corn flakes. Place chicken skin side up in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake for 50 minutes or until done.

title: onion cheese pie
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Pour over onion mixture.
Add cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serve warm over salad.

title: quick spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Chill thoroughly. Serve with corn chips or your favorite chips.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs; mix in milk and mustard. Add sausage and cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange cubed bread on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chimichangas
directions: Place large tablespoon of seasoned meat on each tortilla. Fold up bottom to cover the filling.
Fold sides toward the center; roll up from bottom.
Use toothpicks to hold the shape. Fry in 350° oil (about 1-inch deep) for 1 minute.
Serve with salsa or guacamole.

title: hamburger and potatoes
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
In a bowl combine onion, hamburger and mushroom soup.
Grease (lightly) a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Layer potatoes on bottom, then both of the cheeses.
Last you add the hamburger mixture.
Keep repeating layers until you use all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar, white sugar, oleo and Crisco until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and beat. Add egg and beat well.
Add flour and soda. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: buffet vegetable bake
directions: Cook peas and carrots and beans until just barely tender. Drain.
Combine with water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Combine remaining ingredients, except crumbs, for sauce.
Toss with vegetables.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Pull chicken apart into bite size pieces. Layer broccoli and chicken in baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix soup and dressing; pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix
oil,
garlic
salt
and
dill
seed
in bowl.
Add dressing dry; stir well.
Keep in bowl for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes,
then pour out in brown bag to let oil soak up for 3 to 4 hours.

title: oriental pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta to al dente and drain well.
Meanwhile, in saucepan, stir red pepper and oils over medium heat for 2 minutes. Add honey, soy sauce and salt.
Stir to combine and mix well with cooked pasta.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, add cilantro, chicken, peanuts and green onions to pasta.
Toss together and garnish with cilantro.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Put uncooked rice in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Brown pork chops and lay on top of rice.
Put one slice onion, tomato and green pepper on each pork chop.
Pour undiluted broth over everything and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Break one loaf of bread into bits on bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over broken bread.
Break second loaf on top and let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until a soft peak forms and set aside.
Boil sugar, water and syrup until mixture forms a firm ball when a small amount is dropped in a cup of water.
Pour thin stream into the egg white mixture, beating constantly until it loses the gloss.
Add nuts.
Spoon onto wax paper or foil.
Top each piece with a pecan half.

title: christmas punch
directions: Stir cranberry juice, pineapple juice and almond flavoring together.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Makes 30 servings.

title: baked rigatoni
directions: Cook sausages in skillet slowly (15 minutes).
Set aside to cool.
Drain some of the grease, leaving enough to saute peppers, onions and garlic until tender.
Add Italian sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cut sausages diagonally into slices and add to sauce. Reheat.
Cook rigatoni in salted water.
Drain.
Layer pasta and sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, starting with sauce and ending with sauce.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove.
Layer cheese slices on top and return to oven to melt cheese.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and Crisco oil until light and fluffy.
Add one egg at a time and flavor.
Sift cake flour with baking soda and salt.
Spoon into creamed mixture, adding milk alternately, with about 3 tablespoons saved for last.
Place in tube baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cut and layer first 4 ingredients in a 10 x 12-inch pan.
Top with raw hamburger.
Pour tomatoes over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible chicken 'n broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion.
Put in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake longer to melt cheese (1 to 2 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham and potato chowder
directions: Melt margarine in 3 1/2-quart casserole.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add potatoes, 2 cups water, salt, paprika and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Combine flour and 1/3 cup water in small bowl; blend well.
Stir into potato mixture.
Add milk.
Simmer until slightly thickened stirring frequently.
Add corn and ham; heat through.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for about 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix
all
of
above
ingredients.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 350°
for
hour
and 15 minutes until top is golden brown. May
1/2 recipe for smaller casserole. Drain corn well for best results.

title: mrs. virginia little's millionaire pie
directions: Combine ingredients and stir well.
Pour in pie crust and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hunter's favorite chili
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat; remove from heat and set aside. In large skillet, cook onions, green peppers and celery in bacon fat until tender. Add vegetable mixture and all remaining ingredients, except beans. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover. Simmer 1 hour to blend flavors.
Stir in beans. Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes longer.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix sugar, onion, catsup and mustard with beans.
Put in a baking dish; lay bacon across top.
Cover and bake 20 minutes; uncover and continue baking for 20 more minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: stellar's cakes
directions: Stir until moistened (like pancake mix).
Grease and flour muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and layer on bottom of bowl.
Mix Cool Whip and Jell-O pudding.
Layer Cool Whip mixture and cookie crumbs until bowl is full.
Serves 15 or more people.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients in a medium bowl with a hand beater until smooth.
(For thinner pancakes, stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons of additional milk.)
Grease a heated griddle, if necessary, with shortening.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the hot griddle.
Cook until pancakes are puffed and dry around edges.
Turn and cook other sides until golden brown.
Serve with applesauce, if desired.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven with water to cover; add the onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Simmer for approximately 1 hour. Melt butter, flour and milk to form a paste.
Gradually add 2 cups broth, then soup.
Place boned chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 450° until bubbly.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Place biscuits on top; cook until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Thinly slice zucchini and cook until tender, as you saute onions in 3/4 stick oleo in a large skillet.
When zucchini is done, drain and set aside.
When onions are golden, add can of chicken soup with water, sour cream and grated raw carrots.
Mix well and add zucchini (drained) and stir well.
Put 1 stick oleo in another pan; let melt and add the package of dressing mix. Coat dressing well with oleo.
Put 1/2 of dressing mix in
a 4-quart casserole, then pour in squash mixture.
Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made day ahead and warmed to serve.

title: "it" chicken
directions: Put rice, dry onion soup mix, mushroom soup, water and mushroom buttons in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Stir until well mixed.
Brown chicken breasts in oleo and pour remaining oleo over rice mixture.
Place chicken breasts over top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bay scallops with tomato-chive cream
directions: Peel and mince the shallot and garlic.
Mince the parsley. In a small pan, combine the tomato sauce, heavy cream, shallot, garlic and parsley.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer over low heat, about 2 minutes.
Whisk in butter, one tablespoon at a time. Squeeze in 1 teaspoon of lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon of salt; stir in chives and parsley.
Cover and keep warm.
Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 400°.
Put scallops in a baking pan and bake until just cooked, about 5 minutes.
Transfer scallops to warmed plates.
Spoon sauce over scallops and serve immediately.
Makes 4 appetizer servings.

title: stage coach chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing and egg in a bowl.
Set aside.
Rinse chicken with water and drain well.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Dip each piece in the salad dressing and egg mixture, then roll in cornflake crumbs.
Arrange chicken pieces in a baking dish or pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to an hour or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy apple bake
directions: Unroll crescents and separate dough into 16 triangles. Cut each apple into eight wedges. Wrap a crescent dough triangle around each apple wedge. Place on greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.

title: pink stuff
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions (any color).
Let it partially set.
In the blender, put yogurt.
Blend.
Pour into a bowl and put in refrigerator.
Let set.
Use as a light dessert or refreshing snack.
Children will go for it.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook chicken in water, then remove it to cool, saving broth. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Meantime, cook onions, pepper and celery in butter in a large skillet until tender. Add tomatoes, soup and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted. Add chicken, spaghetti and peas. Mix well. Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 pan or casserole dish. Bake for 40 minutes or until bubbly. May be frozen prior to baking. Serves 8.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Roll chicken in powdered dressing and put on top rack of barbecue grill with skin side up.
Cook on low for 1 hour or golden in color.
Don't turn.

title: cookie sundae pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
When the pie shell is cooled, fill with 1 quart of yogurt, ice cream or Dairy Queen.
Place in freezer.
Cut and serve.

title: pork hot dish
directions: In a skillet, heat oil.
Cook pork, celery, peppers and onion until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
In large bowl, combine pork mixture and next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine crumbs and oleo and sprinkle on top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries with juice, pineapple with juice and mashed bananas.
Pour 1/2 in 8 x 10-inch Pyrex pan.
Then cover with sour cream or yogurt. Then add remaining 1/2 mixture.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut drop cookies
directions: Cream
together
shortening
and sugar; add beaten eggs and blend thoroughly.
Sift flour; add baking powder and salt. Add milk to creamed mixture; add nuts and mix enough to blend. Drop with
teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 350° about
minutes.
Makes	about
dozen.
Can put pecans instead of peanuts.

title: lemon-raspberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In a small bowl, mix eggs, buttermilk, oil and lemon extract. Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in raspberries.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes or until center of muffin springs back when lightly touched.
Yields 15 muffins.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In a heavy 3-quart pan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water. Boil, stirring constantly, until clear.
Remove from heat; stir in Jell-O.
Cool.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mary's baked brisket
directions: Wash brisket; pat dry with paper towel.
Place in a large, glass, deep baking dish (9 x 11-inch or larger), with the lean side down in pan.
Use amount of seasoning according to taste. Cover with foil and bake in a 325° preheated oven for at least 2 hours.
Turn brisket, fat side down.
Continue to cook covered for at least 2 more hours or until done.

title: easy sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and use to cover chicken. Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts into cubes, then place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 1/2 cheese.
Mix soup with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Mix stuffing with melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Then bake another 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Place chicken in cake pan and sprinkle with salt.
Blend sour cream, soup and sherry; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry-raisin bake(scones)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a round 9-inch cake pan.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Using a fork, cut in butter until coarse crumbs are formed.
Add the milk, eggs and raisins. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
With floured hands, pat 1/2 of the dough into the greased cake pan.
Press dough 1/4-inch on the sides of pan.
Spread strawberry jam on top dough.
Use remainder of dough, spreading evenly.
Using a sharp knife, score dough into 8 wedges.
Brush top lightly with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Combine gelatin, cold water and boiling water.
Chill until it is like unbeaten egg white.
Fold in yogurt and whipped topping. Pour into crust and refrigerate.
Nonfat yogurt and light whipped topping and sugar-free lemon gelatin may be used.

title: tortellini in herb garlic dressing
directions: Mix oil and vinegar together until well mixed. Stir in garlic, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over tortellini. Add basil, parsley and scallions (chopped fine).
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup finely grated Parmesan to serve chilled.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat in large pot sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Begin with a large bowl as the batter is huge.
Put oil in bowl.
Add brown sugar and then eggs.
Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with the buttermilk.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Flavor improves the second day.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening (butter), eggs, sugar and flavoring. Blend in flour. Cover bowl and chill in freezer at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°. Roll dough on lightly floured board. Cut into desired shapes. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 6 to 8 minutes. Decorate as desired.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: mary's peach cobbler
directions: In a pan about 9 x 13-inch, melt a stick of butter in the bottom.
Then take four medium cans of peaches and dump them, juice and all, into pan.
Take a box of Duncan Hines yellow cake mix and sprinkle it over the peaches and juice.
Spread the mix and pat it down gently.
Then make a few holes with a fork so the juice can come up to the top.
Melt another stick of butter and dribble it over the top of the cake mix.
Add a dash of nutmeg and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix
cake mix, sugar, eggs, oil and buttermilk together well. Pour
into	9
x
13-inch
pan.
Mix
the
brown sugar, cinnamon, nuts and raisins well.
Swirl mixture through batter already in pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in a plastic bag with all other ingredients. Shake to coat chicken completely.
Remove chicken from bag and place on baking sheet coated with no-stick cooking spray.
Also lightly spray top of chicken.
Bake at 425° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour or until chichen is tender and golden brown.

title: kahlua mocha coffee slush
directions: Put coffee, milk and ice in blender.
Blend until slushy.
Add ice cream and blend 3 seconds.
Add Kahlua to taste and blend a second more and pour into glasses.

title: confetti meat loaf
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In foil-lined baking pan, shape beef mixture into an 8 x 5-inch loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
If desired, serve with tomato sauce over top.
Serves 4 to 6.
Yum!

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix butter and crumbs.
Press in cake pan.
Mix pudding and other ingredients all together and spread on Ritz crackers.
Let stand in refrigerator 1/2 hour and cover with Dream Whip.
You can save some crumbs and put on top.

title: jello candy
directions: Pour in shallow pan and cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season beef.
Saute in skillet; drain and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients; mix well.
Spoon half of batter into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Place cooked beef over top of batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Stir butter until softened; beat in egg.
Stir in orange juice and orange rind.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add wet ingredients and beat well.
Stir in nuts and raisins (or dates).
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and store in tightly covered container. Yield:
2 dozen.
Contain 80 calories each.

title: burgers and vegetables
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salt and pepper well and shape into patties.
Fry until done.
Stir together soup, water, worcestershire sauce, carrots and green beans.
Simmer approximately 20 minutes.

title: butter pecan turtle squares
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter.
Add 1 cup brown sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer.
Gradually add flour, mixing well. Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and set aside.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and oleo.
Work into fine crumbs. Remove 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Mix boiling water, molasses and baking soda.
Add remaining crumbs; mix well.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining cup of crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.
I like it when hot, topped with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: veal cutlet parmigiana(parmigiana di vitello e cotolette)
directions: Prepare veal cutlets.
Line
baking
dish with layer of tomato sauce and
sprinkle
with
Parmesan
cheese
and ground pepper. Place a layer of veal cutlets on tomato sauce.
Place a 1/4-inch slice
of Mozzarella cheese on each cutlet.
Sprinkle with a little pepper and cover with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake,
uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with cooked spaghetti, if desired.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce, green peppers, celery and green onions.
Using a large glass or plastic bowl, layer lettuce (at the bottom), peppers, celery, green onions, frozen peas (do not thaw) and water chestnuts.
Spread mayonnaise over the top layer.
Make sure to seal your mayonnaise layer to the edge of the bowl.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the mayonnaise.
Add nuts, bacon bits or dried onion rings to the top.
Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: carrots parmesan
directions: Boil carrots until tender in salted water to which sugar is added.
Drain and finely chop.
In a blender or food processor, mix carrots and cream.
Add Parmesan cheese and season to taste. Pour mixture into large greased casserole dish.
Spread grated onion on top and arrange pecan halves over the top of all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer. Pour everything over shredded beef.
Mix altogether.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer.
(Serves 20 people.)

title: cheddar-artichoke crescents
directions: Utensil: Cut-N-Seal pastry cutter.

title: corn chip dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and refried beans.
Put in middle of plate.
Top with sour cream.
Garnish with vegetables and cheese. Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Spray 13x9 in baking dish with Pam. Place vegetables in prepared dish. Spray vegetables with Pam for 10 seconds; toss until evenly coated. Bake 30-35 min. until vegetables are browned and tender, stirring after 15 min. Drizzle with honey then sprinkle with salt and cinnamon. Makes 8 servings.

title: grannie's bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear bread into pieces, putting into pan also.
Pour eggs over and sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour a small amount of milk and stir.
Pour rest in.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Mix flour and garlic salt; coat eggplant in this mixture.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown, turning once.
Pour half of tomato sauce into an ungreased 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add eggplant and Parmesan cheese.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over eggplant; sprinkle with oregano and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Will serve 4.

title: grannie's molasses cake
directions: Mix together the first six ingredients and set aside.
In separate pan, mix shortening into boiling water.
Add baking soda, then combine the mixtures.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: dainty cucumber sandwiches
directions: Put onion and cucumber in blender until finely chopped.
Add cream cheese, seasonings and food coloring.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into assorted shapes.
Spread filling on half pieces. Top with remaining pieces.
Makes about 8 dozen.
Great for summer parties.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine pancake mix, corn and water.
Stir to blend thoroughly. Deep fry or heat 1/4-inch oil in a skillet.
Drop 1 tablespoon batter into hot oil.
Fry 4 to 5 minutes, turning once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peaches delight
directions: Spread wafer crumbs in 2-quart buttered dish; save 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix eggs, butter and powdered sugar together.
Pour in crumbed pie shell.
Fold in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Pour egg mixture with pineapple.
Cover with crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and top with 12 Ritz crackers, crushed and a little melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple-glazed chick 'n' grits gorgonzola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flatten chicken breast between waxed paper.
Place chicken in baking pan coated with cooking spray. Combine next 5 ingredients (apple butter to blk. pepper).
Brush over chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cut chicken into 1/2 inch slices.
Spoon Gorgonzola grits into 4 shallow serving bowls.
Top with chicken.
Sprinkle with green onion tops.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into shallow baking dish which has been buttered.
Put in tablespoon of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour or until it starts to bake away from the sides of dish.
Baking time depends on thickness of corn mixture in dish.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil, combine with next 4 ingredients.
Layering; add salt and pepper to each layer. Sprinkle top with olive oil.
Cover; simmer 35 to 45 minutes, uncover and continue to heat 10 minutes.
Flavor is best if allowed to stand awhile or made ahead.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into a greased 12 muffin tin holder.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil together 9 cups water and 4 cups sugar; add Jell-O to hot mixture. When thoroughly mixed, add 4 cups cold water, then add all ingredients, except ginger ale or Sprite! Freeze overnight or longer; remove 1 hour before serving. Stir with a fork and let the punch thaw to slush. Add ginger ale or Sprite.

title: steffie cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in
small balls and press out on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° to
for
10 to 15 minutes. Makes 125 cookies.

title: pea salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine drained peas, diced dill pickle spears, diced cheese and Miracle Whip. Stir gently until evenly mixed. Refrigerate.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: angel flake rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Mix sugar, soda and flour together.
Blend in shortening.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk; mix.
Part can be rolled out and cooked.
The remaining can be put into covered bowl in refrigerator.
Later can be rolled out and cooked as needed.
Bake at 475°.
Regulate for best results.

title: orange piquant
directions: Drain oranges, reserving 1 tablespoon syrup.
Combine 1 tablespoon syrup and marmalade.
Heat until marmalade melts.
Place oranges in dessert dishes.
Spoon marmalade over.
Trim with sour cream or whipped cream.
Serves 2.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix together soup, butter, sour cream, cheese, salt and onion.
Pour over potatoes. Top with corn flakes. Drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over all and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar;
add
eggs,
mixing
well. Add all dry ingredients
and
nuts.
Shape into rolls; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Slice with a knife dipped in water.
Slice
thin and bake on greased cookie sheet until brown at
Rolls may be kept in refrigerator several days and baked as needed.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix sour cream, curry powder and chili sauce together; let stand in the refrigerator to blend flavoring.
Clean and cut up raw vegetables of your taste.

title: aebleskiver
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, salt and milk; then add flour, soda and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Last, fold in stiffly
beaten egg whites.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: a real tasty chicken dish
directions: Layer bacon on bottom of baking dish; add chicken.
Sprinkle onion on top of chicken.
Combine sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.
Top with a generous layer of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: mom's mealtime meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ketchup; put in loaf pan. Top with ketchup.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Drain strawberries, reserving juice.
Set aside.

title: chocolate tornado
directions: Spoon whipped topping evenly into 6 dessert dishes.
Make a depression in the center; spread topping up sides of dishes. Prepare pudding as directed.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon into the center of whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: flan (caramel custard)
directions: Melt 1 cup of sugar in 1 1/2-quart dish and cook, stirring constantly, until sugar caramelizes.
Remove from heat and tip dish back and forth to coat with caramel.
Let cool while combining remaining 1/2 cup sugar, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla. Blend well.
Strain if necessary and gently pour into caramel coated dish.
Cover dish; set in pan of hot water and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
While still hot, turn out on serving plate.
To flame adult portions, pour hot brandy over flan and light.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: three layer salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let set until firm.
Whip cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Together and put on first layer.
Cook in microwave until thickened, 1 minute at a time, on High.
Stir and continue 1 more minute, etc.
Cool and layer on cheese mixture. Chill and serve.

title: shrimp pate
directions: Beat together until mixed well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Press with a spoon until blended.
Put remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stop stirring and boil 1 minute.
Add to the peanut butter mixture.
Stir; when slightly cool, dampen hands and roll into balls.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: delicious chicken dish
directions: Simmer breasts 30 minutes.
Drain and bone; arrange in baking dish.
Melt butter; saute mushrooms and stir in flour.
Add seasonings, milk and broth.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: boar chops in mustard
directions: Season the chops with salt and pepper. Roll in flour and brown in hot vegetable oil in a skillet.
Add the cognac and light this with a match.
Douse the flame with the wine.
Add mustard and cook, covered, until the meat is tender.
Add the sour cream and cook a few minutes longer.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, beat well.
Pour into 2 small unbaked pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 275° then 50 minutes at 300°.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook artichoke hearts according to package directions.
Cool and slice into slivers.
Combine macaroni, tomatoes, olives and artichoke hearts into a large bowl.
Make a dressing of the oil and vinegar.
Pour over salad.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: italian-swiss meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together, except for ham and cheese.
After mixing, shape into a rectangle and place ham down and then Swiss cheese.
Roll loaf and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
(Add more bread crumbs, if necessary.)

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together in saucepan the gelatine, sugar and salt.
Add water and stir over medium heat until gelatine and sugar are completely dissolved.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Chill until firm in mold or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange sorbet
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, combine orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and orange peel.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Pour into large bowl.
Cool to room temperature.
In medium bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg white until stiff peaks form. Gently fold into orange juice.
Pour mixture into a shallow, metal pan.
Freeze 2 hours or until partially frozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and corn syrup until it threads.
Add butter and peanuts; cook slowly to 300°, stirring occasionally.
Add soda and vanilla.
(It will foam up.) Turn out onto two buttered baking sheets; pull out thin as it cools.
When cold, break into pieces with knife handle.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: pasta with zucchini
directions: Heat oil in wide frying pan over high heat.
Add garlic and zucchini; cook and stir until zucchini is tender-crisp (3 to 4 minutes).
Reduce heat to low.
While zucchini is cooking, cook linguine in 3 quarts of boiling water until tender to bite.
Drain well and set aside.

title: cherry cheesecake brownies
directions: Mix
brownies as directed
and
bake
minutes.
Mix cream cheese until fluffy,
add
remaining ingredients, except pie filling, to cream cheese
and pour over brownies.
Bake 25 more minutes or until set.
Cool,
pour pie filling on top and chill.

title: honey butter
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields about 1 cup of butter.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except spareribs.
When thoroughly mixed, place spareribs into sauce.
Soak in mixture for 1 hour, turning frequently.
Remove ribs to rack in roasting pan. Place small amount of water in pan.
Roast in oven at 325° to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning from time to time.
Serves 4.

title: double-layer pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pudding mix and 1 1/3 cups milk in large saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thick and comes to full boil, stirring constantly with wire whisk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pumpkin and spices, using wire whisk.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture returns to boil.
Remove from heat.
Let cool 20 minutes or until almost cool.
Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Spread cooled pudding mixture over cheese mixture. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers; mix all together except coconut.
Roll into marble size balls, then roll into coconut or just powdered sugar. Can freeze.
Let thaw 5 minutes and serve.
Good for parties.

title: baked chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and Italian seasoning, mixing well.
Dip chicken in melted butter and coat with crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sam's chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a very large pan, side by side.
Mix soups together and pour over chicken.
May be a little lumpy. Bake 3 hours at 250°.
Serve the gravy over rice.

title: g s i old-fashioned bean soup
directions: Drain beans which have been picked, washed and soaked overnight.
Refresh with cold water.
Drain again.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Put on stove.
Boil for 15 or 20 minutes after they start boiling.
Put in jars.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread out on baked crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
When set, spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Serve topped with whipped topping and a sprinkle of coconut.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and add onion together.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook until soup is ready.
Serve in bowls garnished with:

title: rice tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Melt remaining butter.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Spray baking dish or pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: stir and drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets with nonstick spray. Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour in wet ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes until soft.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling water until tender but not mushy.
Drain the cooked potatoes, saving 1 1/2 cups of the liquid.
Fry the salt pork in a skillet until browned.
Remove the pork from the skillet and set aside.
Add the onions, carrots, and celery to the skillet and saute in the drippings until the vegetables are soft but not browned.
In a large Dutch oven combine the potatoes, reserved potato water, salt pork, the sauteed vegetables, and the corn.
Bring this mixture to a boil and then immediately reduce the heat.
Simmer for about 5 minutes. Taste and add salt and black pepper as needed.
Add the zucchini and continue cooking over low heat until zucchini is tender.
Add the cream slowly.
Cook just until the cream is heated.

title: stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat in hot oil in large skillet until browned.
Add broccoli mixture; stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic powder and ginger; add to skillet.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve stir-fry over rice.
Serves 4.

title: cardinal chicken salad
directions: Mix together the apples in the lemon juice, chicken, celery, salad dressing, grapes, salt and pepper.
Put in 1/2-quart pan. Mix cream cheese, 1/4 of Miracle Whip and put cheese mixture on top of the other mixture.
Freeze and slice.

title: 8 layer salad
directions: Make the night before.

title: chicken and vegetables with tofu
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2 inch cubes and chicken into thin strips. Mix 1 tablespoons each cornstarch and soy sauce, sherry and garlic; stir in chicken.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Blend broth, vinegar, remaining cornstarch and soy sauce.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in hot wok or skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry 2 minutes; remove.
Heat remaining oil in same wok.
Add next 4 ingredients and whites of green onions; stir-fry 2 minutes. Add green onion tops; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add chicken and broth mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Fold in tofu; heat through.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and salt in top of a double boiler.
Stir in scalded milk; cover and cook until mixture thickens (do not let water boil in bottom of pot).
Stir in well beaten egg yolks and cook until mixture is quite thick.
Add vanilla.
Line a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Add cooked custard and banana slices in layers.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat each thoroughly.
Add the drained pineapple, then fold in bread cubes. Bake in 1 1/2-quart (greased) casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be served with lemon sauce as dessert.
Excellent with ham.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and egg; pat in pan.
Mix together sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
Mix will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Mix will fall in middle.

title: fried rice
directions: Chop green pepper, carrots and onion very fine.
Cook in a skillet with oil.
Add beaten eggs, vegetables and meat (chopped small).
When cooked a little, mix in rice and seasonings.
Just before serving, add soy sauce.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift together sifted flour, salt, baking powder and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add shortening and milk.
Mix and roll out thin on a floured board.
Peel apples and cut up fine on pastry. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter (cut up fine).
Roll up like a jelly roll and slice 2 inches thick. Place in a greased baking pan, cut side up.
Place sauce around dumplings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients by hand.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let cool before cutting.

title: green garden salad
directions: Add lemon gelatin to 1 cup boiling water.
Mix; let cool.
Mix mayonnaise and milk well. Add to gelatin and vinegar mix.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to gel.
Add vegetable mix.
Place in mold and return to refrigerator.
When salad is hard, turn over and serve.

title: overnight chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken and salt for 1 hour.
Bone chicken and chop meat coarsely.
Cook broccoli; drain well.
Arrange in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Combine next seven ingredients; spoon half of sauce over broccoli.
Arrange chicken over sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 8.

title: honey baked chicken breasts
directions: In a small bowl, mix honey, mustard, onion, curry powder and garlic.
Arrange chicken in a baking pan and brush with honey sauce, then sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and turn chicken.
Brush with remaining sauce. Return to oven and continue baking for about 30 minutes more.

title: lizzies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet or into mini-muffin tins that have been well sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 250° oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a well-greased, large casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stir-fry imitation crab
directions: Soak dried mushrooms in warm water until softened.
Discard stems and slice thin.
Squeeze excess water.
Heat oil in wok or frying pan.
Saute ginger and garlic until golden; discard. Stir-fry mushrooms and broccoli until crisp-tender.
Mix sake, shoyu sauce, cornstarch and broth and add to broccoli.
Add salt; stir.
Stir in crab.
Heat and serve.

title: infatica koosa (koosa stew)
directions: Dice vegetables.
Brown meat and onions in a Dutch oven.
Add peppers and Koosa and stir.
Add tomato paste, spices to taste, and enough water to cover.
Let mixture come to a boil, then simmer and cover until vegetables are tender (approximately 45 minutes). Serve over rice if preferred.

title: ham chowder
directions: Cook carrots, celery, onion and potatoes in 5 cups water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add ham, butter, salt and pepper. Blend flour into milk smoothly; stir into soup.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Turn heat to low and allow to simmer, partially covered, 10 to 20 minutes to develop flavor. Serve with hot garlic bread and a tossed salad.

title: peter pan choco surprises
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add gradually until well blended.
Chill dough at least 30 minutes for easier handling.

title: broccoli fish au gratin
directions: Place broccoli in a 2 pt. shallow baking dish.
Place fish on top.
Blend soup and milk and pour over the fish.
Put cheese over soup mixture.
Mix butter, seasoning, and crumble bagels together and place on top.
Bake at 450 for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip. Place in graham cracker crust. Chill.
Pie freezes well.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix instant pudding, buttermilk, mandarin oranges and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and crushed cookies. Chill and serve.

title: pronto puppies
directions: Heat deep fat to 375°.
Blend egg and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Dip frankfurters in batter.
Fry until brown, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Serve on cocktail toothpicks.
To reheat, place in 400° oven about 5 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet and drain.
Remove half and set aside.
