Add Ragu to skillet; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, mix Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese, egg, remaining sausage and parsley.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter; pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned. Cool.
Chill thoroughly, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine very well.
Add melted chocolate. Add one egg at a time and beat well after each.
Add vanilla and beat.
Caution:
Be sure to beat until all grainy consistency is gone.
Pour into baked pastry shell; cool in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours or longer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Refrigerate.
This will not be a firm congealed salad, but similar to whole cranberry sauce.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni per instructions.
Blend tomatoes; add to rice.
Brown beef; add to rice.
Simmer slowly for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for a glass dish).
Slice peaches.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and set aside for 1 hour or so.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in milk and almond extract.
Melt butter in deep baking dish.
Pour batter into dish.
Do not stir.
Pour peaches over batter; do not stir.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm with cream (whipped), plain ice cream or just plain.
Serves 6 polite or 4 hungry ones.

title: microwave pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix as directed on package, substituting pineapple juice for the water.
Melt butter in microwaveproof cake or pie dish, about 30 to 45 seconds.
Mix brown sugar with butter. Arrange pineapple and cherries on top of butter and brown sugar mixture.
Pour cake batter over top of brown sugar, pineapple and cherries in dish.
Cover with a paper towel or waxed paper. Micro-bake 9 to 11 minutes on Medium-high, rotating once.

title: odell's flour tortillas
directions: Mix first three ingredients together well.
Add lard or shortening and mix well.
Add about 1/2 cup warm water, little by little (or more, just to mix).
Make the dough so it can be rolled--not too soft.
Roll in hands into small balls.
Place in bowl to set for a while.
Cover with cloth or Saran Wrap.
After setting, roll into tortillas and cook on both sides.

title: english trifle
directions: Cut cake in fingers, 1-inch thick.
Butter them on one side. Place the fingers, buttered side down, in bottom of a large bowl which can be used to serve the dessert in.
Spread top with jam and over this pour the sherry.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Let stand.

title: butter divinity
directions: Combine sugar, salt, syrup and water; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Boil to 262° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; pour slowly over egg whites, beating with electric mixer.
Continue beating for 5 minutes. Mixture will be very stiff.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat by hand until firm.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken celery casserole
directions: Combine melted margarine and cracker crumbs, set aside.
Cook celery in small amount of water until crisp-tender.
Saute onion in small amount of margarine until tender.
Combine soups, water chestnuts, pimiento and cheese.
Mix well.
Stir in celery, onion and chicken.
Pour into lightly greased baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs, then almonds.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: broccoli-bacon-cheese salad
directions: Cut up broccoli in bite-size pieces.
Cook pan crispy; then crumble into tiny pieces.
Add onion, bacon, cheese and broccoli in large bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour dressing over top of broccoli mixture.
Stir and enjoy.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown beef in skillet and drain. Add onions to beef and brown. Salt and pepper to taste. Layer in bottom of casserole. Cover meat and onions. Next, add mashed potatoes, then Cheddar cheese. Place in oven and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: kourambiethes(greek butter finger cookies)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Pour butter into mixer bowl. Discard sediment.
Chill until firm.
Beat until light and creamy. Add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, orange juice and egg yolk; beat well.
Beat in 3 cups cake flour.
Stir in remaining 1 cup cake flour. Stir in almonds.
Stir in enough all-purpose flour to form soft dough that is not sticky.
Shape into small crescents; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Remove to wire rack; sprinkle with additional confectioners sugar while warm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into thumb sized balls. Chill and serve.

title: san antonio spinach salad
directions: Combine vegetables, beans and bacon in large bowl.
Combine picante sauce, dressing and cumin in small bowl; mix well.
Pour picante sauce mixture over vegetables; toss lightly to coat with dressing.
Garnish with eggs, if desired, and serve with additional picante sauce.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins and drain.
Mix and sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine sugar, molasses, beaten egg, and milk with melted shortening and mix well.
Add flour and oatmeal gradually.
Add raisins.
Drop from a teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 3 doz. cookies.

title: chicken-soy stir-fry(serves 4)
directions: *I use Market Day chicken steaks and broccoli florets!! Takes only 15 minutes to prepare!!

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, vinegar, sugar, salt, onion and hot peppers. Cook 2 hours on medium or medium-high heat.
Cook until you get it to the desired consistency.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend the cream cheese and strawberries.
Stir in fruit and marshmallows.
Add small amount cherry juice.
Pour into 2 (1-quart) containers and freeze overnight.
To serve, let stand at room temperature for a few minutes.
Turn out and slice.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
You may use lite fruits and low-fat mayonnaise for less fat and calories.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine 2 sticks oleo, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; remove from heat. Add soda, salt, flour and sugar; mix well.
Blend in beaten eggs. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into greased 18 x 12-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar. Beat until well blended. Blend in melted butter. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325 degrees for one hour. Remove from oven. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream. Makes one nine inch pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese with a fork until smooth.
Stir pineapple, 1 cup pecans, bell pepper, onion and salt to taste into cheese.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Cover with wax paper and chill.

title: steve's carrot casserole(serves four)
directions: Grate apple and wash cranberries.
Combine with carrots, sugar, salt and cider.
Place in buttered casserole and dot with butter.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes, stirring once.

title: new york city salsa
directions: Combine sour cream, salsa and salad dressing.
Mix well in a bowl.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips and raw veggies.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut in and blend together flour, baking powder, salt, shortening and sugar.
Add gradually cold milk. Use just enough to moisten.

title: christmas morning muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon into small muffin tin.
Bake at 400° until slightly brown.

title: banana punch
directions: Make syrup of sugar and water. Boil for 3 minutes; cool. Mix juice and bananas in blender. Mix all together and freeze in quart container. Add 2 quarts 7-Up to mix about 1 hour before serving. Serves 35.

title: sour cream roll out cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with mixer.
Mix flour and baking powder and add slowly to mixture.
Dough will be stiff.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry delight(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Combine egg and sugar, then add milk, margarine and yeast.
Mix well.
Add flour, then mix.
Cover in refrigerator.
After mixture rises, drop in muffin pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: date rolls
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg and dates (chopped) in saucepan. Cook slowly, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Form in balls or logs.
Roll in coconut.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches with juice into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle instant tapioca over peaches.
Make sure butter is soft and mix it with the cake mix.
It will be crumbly.
Spread the mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: linda's potatoes
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup, sour cream and cheese. Add potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingersnaps
directions: You will need small saucer with sugar for dipping.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all above ingredients into a blender and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
This pie comes out with a pie crust, coconut filling and also a topping.

title: broccoli and cauliflower linguine
directions: Saute the broccoli, cauliflower and garlic in oil for 3 minutes.
Cut tomatoes. Add with juice, salt, basil, pepper and bay leaves.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.
Add sherry.
Continue cooking 3 minutes more. Remove bay leaves. Cook linguine according to label directions; drain.
Toss hot pasta with vegetable mixture, cheese and cilantro.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine soup and cheese and add to onion and celery mixture.
Mix well. Pour sauce, broccoli and rice into buttered casserole dish and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and light brown.
(Mama always says to eat your veggies!)

title: orange frosting
directions: Mix until smooth.
Spread on orange cookies and decorate with raisins, gumdrops, chocolate pieces, etc.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil until peaches are tender.
Put in jars and seal.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, then add egg yolks.
Add flour, soda and baking powder alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in egg whites (beaten) and vanilla.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done by testing.

title: stir-fried broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into 2 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Wash and drain.
In Dutch oven or large skillet over high heat in very hot salad oil, cook broccoli, stirring quickly and frequently (stir-frying) until well coated.
Add 1/4 cup water, salt and sugar.
Reduce heat to medium-high; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Uncover and stir-fry 5 to 6 minutes more until tender-crisp.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add egg and continue to beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients. Save 1/4 cup of dry ingredients; add the rest to the wet mixture. Coat the blueberries with remaining dry ingredients.
Fold blueberries into batter.
This batter is very thick.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: fried chicken and green peppers(servings:  8)
directions: Cut chicken into slightly larger than bite size pieces. Marinate the meat with soy and sherry for 30 minutes and dust with cornstarch.
Cover the meat thoroughly.
Fry the meat for 5 minutes or more until it is done.
Cut the green peppers in about 8 pieces. Each piece should not be bigger than 1 piece of meat.
Heat 1 tablespoon of salad oil in a frying pan and fry the ginger and green peppers for 30 seconds.
Put the chicken together with the prepared sauce back in the pan.
Stir constantly for about 1 to 2 minutes until the chicken soaked in the sauce well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onions in butter.
Stir in soup, sour cream and water.
Simmer 45 minutes or until done.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add butter, oil, sugar and cake mix.
Beat until fluffy.
Add sour cream, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 15.

title: poke greens
directions: Wash poke greens thoroughly.
Place in pan, add water and bring to a boil.
Add soda.
Then drain off soda water.
Add fresh hot water.
Bring back to boiling, lower flame and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Drain and place in skillet with drained spinach and oil. Continue to cook and dip out excess water for a few minutes.
Stir eggs and add to greens and cook until eggs are cooked.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread	cream
cheese
on plate.
Pour chili sauce over top. Chop
olives,
pepper and onion and add on top.
Makes a great party dip.

title: crumb coated potatoes
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the bread crumbs, paprika, salt and pepper. Brush potatoes with butter. Roll in crumb mixture until coated. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar-free chocolate fudge
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, melted chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth. Stir in nuts. Pour into an 8-inch square pan lined with greased foil. Have the foil extend over edge of pan for easy removal. Cover and chill overnight. Cut into 16 squares.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine mushroom soup and cheese. Combine all other ingredients with noodles.
Mix everything together in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: blueberry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pastry shell.
Spoon pie filling carefully over cheese layer.
Chill until set.

title: "dirt"
directions: Mix cream cheese, 10x sugar and margarine thoroughly.
Add milk, pudding mix (dry) and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Make alternating layers of crushed cookies and mixture starting with a layer of cookies.
Make layers as wide as you want.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cok noodles, using package directions; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, pepper, pimiento and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
If desired, top with 1/2 cup toasted, slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes
6 servings.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except filling.
Spread 3/4 of batter on greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling and dab remaining dough over filling and sort of pull together with spoon or spatula (filling will not be completely covered).
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread or cake
directions: Shred or grate zucchini (if done in the blender add 1/2 cup of the oil with it).
Sift together dry ingredients except pudding. Beat sugar and eggs, add oil and blend well. Alternately add dry ingredients and zucchini.
Stir in nuts and coconut, add vanilla and instant pudding.
Pour into 4 miniature pans (3 x 5 x 3-inch) that have been greased well and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika, mustard and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk gradually.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir one minute; stir in corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar, 1 1/2 cups water and vanilla bean for 30 minutes (gentle boil).
Dissolve coffee in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Shake sugar syrup and coffee in bottle.
Add vodka; let stand 2 weeks in covered bottle.
Remove vanilla bean.
Store in tightly covered glass container.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Shred beef in food processor.
Mix all ingredients.
Great with snack crackers.

title: mixed veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a sprayed Pyrex dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and put over Veg-All mixture.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (no longer).

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until brown.
Drain.
Spread in greased 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over other mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs and sour cream.
Blend in flour, salt, soda and powder alternately with bananas.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour bread pan.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together jello and boiling water.
Then add lemonade (undiluted) with cold water and cranberry cocktail.
Mix well. Add ginger ale and ice before serving.
For 80 servings, triple the amounts.

title: almost eggs benedict(diabetic recipe)
directions: In the top of a double boiler over boiling water, combine cheese, dry milk, water and mustard.
Cook, stirring, until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle bacon bits evenly on English muffin halves. Top each half with a poached egg; spoon sauce over eggs.
Serves 2.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.

title: fricasseed chicken
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour, 2 teaspoons salt and paprika.
Coat chicken.
Brown in hot fat.
Add water, onions, bay leaves, celery, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, 1 hour or until tender.

title: macaroni salad
directions: For a summer meal, add a pound of fresh shrimp.

title: hawaiian loaf(sweet bread)
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar until light.
Add eggs beat
well.
Stir in banana.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda.
Add to butter mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in pineapple and coconut.
Spoon
batter into 2 greased and floured 9 by 5 inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350-degree oven until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean,
about 60-70 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, keeping it finely crumbled.
Add onion and saute until onions are tender; remove from heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain, reserving 1/2 cup water. Mix soups, reserved water and milk, beating well, and heat until warm.
Combine noodles, liquids and sausage and onion mixture; pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with stuffing and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
This recipe freezes well.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Heat oil in deep pan or Dutch oven.
Brown chicken, a few pieces at a time, removing from pan as done.
When all chicken is browned, add celery and onion.
Cook until done.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Add peas and carrots.
Return chicken to pot.
Add bouillon and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Cook 25 minutes.

title: english trifle
directions: Place ladyfingers or sliced pound cake in bottom of large glass bowl, making sure bottom is covered and partway up the sides. Drizzle rum or sherry (optional) over cake.
Make jello with 2 cups boiling water (omit 2 cups cold water).
Add raspberries and pour over all of the cake.
Place in refrigerator overnight or until set.
Make custard or pudding according to package.
Let cool and pour over jello.
Return to refrigerator until set.
Whip the cream and place on top before serving.
Decorate as desired.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter a large baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Mix all ingredients except chicken and place in baking pan.
Place chicken pieces on top; brush with melted butter and sprinkle paprika over.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: spinach potato casserole
directions: Beat the potatoes into the remaining ingredients.
Put into casserole and put 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in heavy saucepan.
Boil until mixture reaches a soft ball stage when placed in cold water.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir and quickly place in a prepared buttered candy pan.
Cool and enjoy.

title: sweet crescent rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredient like pie crust.
Add 2 yeast cakes or 2 packages dry yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Stir well, then fill cup with cold milk so that you have 1 cup liquid. Add yeast mixture to flour mixture along with 2 slightly beaten eggs.
Mix well and set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day divide into 4 parts.
Roll out 1 part at a time, like pie crust. Cut into 8 pie shaped pieces. Roll each piece, starting with side side.
Let rise until fingerprint shows (about 1 hour) and bake at 350° about 20 minutes (bake until lightly browned).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix.
Put into casserole.
Cover with small cheese crackers. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Combine the raisins, apricots and apple juice (or rum) in a bowl.
Let soak overnight or for at least 4 hours.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and flour with electric mixer.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into walnut-sized balls and press into ungreased tart pans.
In small bowl, mix egg, butter, vanilla, brown sugar, pecans and salt.
Drop into pastry cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients until dough is formed. Knead dough 5 to 10 times.
Pinch off dough and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beggar man's meal
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish and stir well. Add hamburger and cover dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon thins
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup of sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat hard.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt. Add to mixture and mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet in marble size balls.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Do not prepare pudding, just use the powder as it comes in a box.

title: cheese coated baked potatoes
directions: Butter baking dish.
Scrub, peel and dry potatoes.
Dip in beaten egg yolk, roll
in
grated
cheese and then in bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 1
hour or until crisp and golden on the outside and soft inside.

title: goulash
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in fat until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add beans and rice; mix.
Turn into casserole.
Bake in 250° to 300° oven for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: lemon mousse pie
directions: In small saucepan, combine gelatin, lemon juice and water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over medium heat until dissolved.
Stir in lemon peel and food coloring.

title: harriett's green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, Chinese vegetables and water chestnuts. Combine soup, milk and soy sauce. Add soup mixture to vegetables in casserole. I add a few onions (French fried), also. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Add rest of French fried onions last 10 minutes of baking time. Serves 8 to 10. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: crock-pot chilli
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic in iron skillet; put in crock-pot with all other ingredients, except beans.
Cook on low setting 8 to 10 hours.
Add beans last hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients except nuts and parsley.
Divide mixture in 2, wrap with waxed paper and chill. Roll in nuts and parsley, refrigerate. Take out 15 minutes before serving.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter; add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushroom soup.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.

title: fruit and nut clusters
directions: Line cookie sheets with waxed paper.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chips; stir until smooth.
Stir in almonds, dates and cherries.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets. Garnish each with candied cherry piece.
Refrigerate until set. Store in airtight container in cool place.
Makes 32 candies.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir with fork.
Make into an airy ball.
Put in pie pan and press to make crust.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Place washed sweet potatoes in a large Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Let cool and cut potatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine orange rind and remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Pour over sweet potato slices.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: fiery drumsticks
directions: Combine yogurt and hot sauce in a shallow dish.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours. Drain chicken; discard marinade.
Dredge chicken in bread crumbs. Arrange in 8-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until chicken is done.
Makes 2 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salad oil and vanilla first.
Mix with mixer. Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch sheet pan at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry milkshake
directions: Place in blender and puree, starting and stopping several times until all the berries are pureed.
Serve immediately. Makes two healthy, no-fat, low calorie treats.

title: tommi's famous shrimp toast
directions: Prepare bread by cutting the crust off all sides.
Place all ingredients except bread in a blender and blend to form a thick paste.
Apply paste to one side of bread, thickly if it is to be used as a shrimp entree, thinly for a shrimp appetizer.
Spread on bread and cut bread into quarters to form squares or cut diagonally to form triangles.
(Triangles look larger than squares.)

title: candace's basil cheese loaf
directions: Combine cream cheese and Roquefort in a bowl; mix until smooth. Set aside.
Combine spinach, parsley, basil and garlic in bowl of food processor with motor running.
Slowly drizzle the oil through the feed tube.
Continue processing until smooth.
Transfer the mixture to a bowl, add walnuts and Parmesan cheese; mix thoroughly. Line a 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with plastic wrap, leaving extra wrap hanging over sides.
Spread 1/3 of cheese mixture evenly over bottom of pan.
Next spread half the pesto mixture and arrange a layer of sun dried tomatoes on top.
Repeat cheese, pesto and tomato layers.
Finish with remaining third of the cheese mixture. Cover with overhanging plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: russian dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender; process until smooth. Refrigerate until needed.

title: quick veggie soup
directions: To microwave ground beef, crumble into a microwave-safe colander.
Place colander in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Line a cookie sheet (with sides) with foil.
This makes clean up easier.
Separate graham crackers and lay side by side. Keebler breaks apart easier.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: In a 2-quart shallow baking dish, combine soup, sour cream and pepper; stir until well blended.
Add vegetables, 2/3 cup French fried onions and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: asparagus sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet.
Roll slices of bread as thin as possible with rolling pin.
Trim crusts.
Lay bread squares on work surface and cover with damp towel for 10 minutes.
Cut cheese into fingers about size of asparagus spears. Spread each slice of bread with mustard.
Lay asparagus spear and cheese finger on each slice and roll up.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Brush rolls with butter.
Bake for 10 minutes or until brown and bubbling.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain and add corned beef, cheese, soup and onion.
Pour into casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well, dot with margarine and cook in hot oven (350°) until custard is thick.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together butter or Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients to mixture, alternating with milk and flavorings until all are well mixed together.
Divide the batter into 3 equal portions.
Tint each portion of batter with yellow, green and pink coloring.
Pour pink batter into 10 x 4-inch tube (greased) pan, then pour green batter over pink, then yellow over green batter.
Bake 70 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: melt moment frosting
directions: Put milk in saucepan; add flour to milk.
Cook to stiff paste, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream butter and sugar; add creamed mixture to cooked paste.
Add vanilla and whip until consistency of whipped cream.
Put frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Blend all together until well mixed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish. Mix sugar and flour.
Add milk, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over oleo in pan but do not stir. Add fruit and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is brown.

title: muffins(apple and carrot)
directions: Whip egg; add applesauce, oil and milk.
Mix with fork.
Mix in separate bowl all the powdered ingredients.
Then mix in apples and carrots.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: special k treats
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and oleo to rolling boil.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Add 4 cups of Special K cereal.
Mix well and drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning to hamburger, following directions on packet.
Add refried beans to hamburger and spread on top of cream cheese.
Put salsa on top of meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Heat at 375° until cheese melts (about 10 minutes).
Serve with tortilla chips.
Add
jalapeno peppers, if desired.

title: ruth griffin's crackling bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients.
Place in hot skillet greased with oil.
Cook until brown.

title: easy almond brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook over medium heat, stirring until color changes, 10 to 12 minutes.
Spread on foil.
Salt lightly. Cool and break in pieces.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Dry well.
Roll out thin and cut into long strips.

title: apple-cheese casserole
directions: Place apples in 1-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over apples.
Bak at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: polynesian coleslaw
directions: Combine pineapple juice with mayonnaise.
Combine cabbage, seasonings and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Serves 6.

title: pralines
directions: Combine pudding mix, brown sugar, evaporated milk and butter in medium size sauce pan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Then cook, without stirring, to 238°.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans.
Beat with wooden spoon 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: strawberry-lemon mold
directions: Mix package of strawberry Jell-O with one cup boiling water. Let stand until cool.
Add one package frozen strawberries.
Put into mold and let stand until firm.
In the meantime, dissolve one package lemon jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Chill until slightly jelled.
Add softened cream cheese and whip with electric mixer.
Fold in Dream Whip (already mixed).
Place on top of firm strawberry mixture.
Keep refrigerated until firm.
Remove from mold right before serving.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and shortening to potatoes while hot.
Combine potato and flour mixture.
Roll or pat to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut out and bake at 425 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple delight
directions: Drain pineapple and use juice with water to make Jello as directed.
Refrigerate Jello for 15-20 minutes.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until it sets.
Add Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts before serving.

title: judy's venison
directions: In aluminum foil, place deer meat.
Cover top with bacon slices.
Slice onion and separate into rings; place this to taste on top of bacon.
Clean peppers and cut into slices or rings. Place on top of onion rings.
Over all, pour Italian dressing. Close aluminum foil tightly and cook at 350° until meat is tender or can be placed on a grill outside and cooked slowly.

title: aunt helen's synthetic brownies
directions: Stir in order given.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a Bundt cake pan.
Chill. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Take a cup of kindness, mix it well with love.
Add a lot of patience and Faith in God Above.
Sprinkle very generously with Joy and Thanks and Cheer, and you'll have a lot of Angel Food to feast upon all year.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Cook grits in boiling water for 5 minutes. Add margarine and cheese.
Stir until melted; remove from heat.
Add milk, eggs and sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: tomato and green bean casserole
directions: Drain tomatoes.
Mix dressing with melted margarine and set aside 3/4 cup for topping. Combine dressing, tomatoes, drained cooked green beans, sugar and seasonings.
Mix and put in a greased shallow baking dish, about 8 x 8-inch.
Sprinkle with reserved dressing. Cover and bake
at 375° for about 35 minutes. Remove cover the last 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: fish chowder
directions: In large pot, brown salt pork in 1 teaspoon butter.
Add onion and stir and cook.
Pour in water and clam juice; bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Add potatoes and pepper; turn to low heat and simmer, partially covered, 15 minutes.
Add fish and simmer until fish flakes and breaks up.
Add milk, remaining butter, thyme and salt.
Stir; bring to simmer over moderate heat.

title: witch's crystal garden(grow your own)
directions: Put two drops of food coloring on the brick or charcoal.
Mix together remaining ingredients and slowly pour onto brick.
Enough for 4 to 6 bricks.
The garden will begin to grow into weird and wonderful shapes in a few drops.
